In a bowl, mix the custard powder and 3 tbsp milk. In a saucepan, bring the vanilla pod and seeds, remaining milk and 1/2 cup sugar to a boil. Remove the vanilla pod, then stir in the custard. Simmer for 1 min, then allow to cool.
Spread the jam onto the pastry base. Spoon over the custard and smooth out, then top with the blueberries. Chill for 4 hours. Dust with powdered sugar to serve.

title: dark chocolate fruit cakes
directions: Combine dried fruit and 1/3 cup sherry. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside for 4 hours to plump.
Preheat oven to 325°F. Grease and line 2 - 6 inch square cake pans with 2 layers of parchment paper.

Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well between each addition. Add plumped fruit and chocolate. Sift in flour and cinnamon and mix until combined. Distribute between prepared pans and smooth surface. Gently press almonds into batter. Bake for 50-55 mins, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Remove from oven and drizzle with extra sherry. Let cool completely in pans.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Place mayonnaise in a medium bowl. Add remaining ingredients and stir well to combine. Season to taste (depending on the acidity of your lemon, you may wish to add a little more lemon juice, too).
Store in a covered container in the refrigerator for 2-3 days.

title: strawberry cobbler bars
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease a 12 x 15 inch baking sheet. Mix the flour, butter, sugar, vanilla extract and a pinch of salt with the dough hook of a mixer, then with your hands to form crumbs. Spread 2/3 of the dough on the baking sheet and press to form a crust. Spread the vanilla pudding and strawberries on top, then sprinkle with the remaining crumbled dough. Bake for 1 hour.
Allow to cool, then cut into 24 squares. Dust with powdered sugar and serve with whipped cream.

title: chili pasta
directions: Cook the pasta in plenty of boiling salted water for 10 mins, until just tender.
Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large skillet on medium. Saute the onion and garlic for 2 mins, until tender. Add the salami strips and cook, stirring for 3 mins.
Stir in beans and tomatoes, and bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer the mixture for 3 mins. Season to taste.
Drain the pasta and return to the pan. Toss with the sauce and basil. Top with feta and serve with bread and salad, if desired.

title: mango jellies with coconut cream
directions: Puree the mango flesh until smooth. You will need 2 cups. Combine the mango puree, lime juice, orange juice and the sugar in a medium saucepan. Simmer, stirring, until the sugar is dissolved. Remove from heat.

Combine the agar agar and 1 1/2 cups hot water in a small saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium; simmer rapidly for 3 mins. Stir to ensure all the agar agar is dissolved. Add agar agar mixture to the warm mango mixture; stir to combine. Pour into six serving glasses. Cover and refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.
To serve, spoon coconut cream over the jellies and drizzle with fresh passionfruit. Decorate sides of glass with fresh pineapple stars or slices of star fruit, if desired.

title: penne napolitana
directions: In a frying pan, heat oil on medium. Cook onion and garlic for 3 mins, stirring, until soft. Add tomatoes and basil and simmer for 15 mins.
Cook penne according to package instructions. Drain.
Top penne with napolitana sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan shavings and extra basil leaves.

title: creepy coconut curry for halloween
directions: Heat half the oil in a wok or large frying pan on high and cook chicken, in two batches, 4-5 mins, turning, until golden all over. Transfer to a plate. Heat remaining oil in same pan and stir-fry onion 3-4 mins, until golden. Add curry paste and cook, stirring, 1 min, until aromatic. Add sweet potato, coconut milk and stock. Return chicken to wok and simmer, partially covered, 8-10 mins, until chicken is just cooked and sweet potato is tender. Mix in broccoli and pineapple and simmer, uncovered, 2-3 more mins. Stir in fish sauce, brown sugar and lime juice. Add tomatoes, top with basil leaves and serve immediately.

title: lamb, pepper, eggplant and pesto stacks
directions: To make the pesto, blend or process cheese, nuts, garlic, basil and 1/4 cup oil until smooth. Stir in lemon juice. Set aside.
Preheat broiler. Broil peppers, skin-side up, until skin blisters and blackens. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside for 5 mins. Peel skin. Broil eggplant slices until tender.
Heat remaining oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook lamb until browned all over and cooked to your liking. Cover and let rest for 5 mins. Slice thickly.
Make stacks of lamb, eggplant and peppers on serving plates. Spoon pesto over top.

title: blueberry sour cream cakes with lemon buttercream
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease and flour two 8-inch cake pans.

Beat the butter, granulated sugar and lemon peel in a large bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, until combined. Stir in 1/2 of the sifted flours and 1/2 of the sour cream. Stir in the remaining flour and sour cream until smooth. Fold in the blueberries. Spread evenly in prepared pans.
Bake for 45-55 mins or until a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pans 5 mins. Remove from pans; cool completely on a wire rack.

For the lemon buttercream, beat the butter, lemon peel and juice, and 1/2 of the powdered sugar in a medium bowl with electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add the remaining sugar and beat for a further 5 mins. Spread over the cooled cakes.

title: turkey tacos
directions: Heat the oil in a large frying pan on high. Brown turkey for 4-5 mins, breaking up with the back of a spoon.
Stir in cumin and chili powder and cook, stirring, for 1 min.
Blend in salsa. Heat taco shells according to pack instructions.
Fill shells with turkey mixture and top with cheese, shredded lettuce and finely chopped tomato. Accompany with sour cream.

title: strawberry ice cream with chocolate and pistachios
directions: In a large metal bowl, mix together the strawberries and sugar and let thaw for 15-20 mins.
Place the strawberry mixture in a blender, add the cream and puree until smooth. Return the mixture to the bowl, then cover and freeze for 15-20 mins.

Melt the chocolate in a metal bowl set over a pan of barely simmering water. Stir until smooth. Remove from the heat and cool for 5 mins. Using an ice cream scoop, divide the ice cream among four dessert dishes. Drizzle over the melted chocolate, then sprinkle with the pistachios. Freeze for 5 mins, then serve.

title: lamb pilaf
directions: Combine ground lamb and breadcrumbs in a medium bowl. Season. Shape into 16 meatballs. Heat 2 tsp oil in a large saucepan over medium heat. Working in batches, cook meatballs for 4-5 mins, or until brown and cooked through. Transfer to a heatproof plate and cover to keep warm.

Add remaining oil to pan. Increase heat to medium-high and cook onion and eggplant, stirring, for 3-4 mins, or until golden brown. Add garlic and spices. Cook, stirring, for 30 seconds, or until fragrant. Add rice and cook, stirring, for 1 min, or until coated in spices. Add stock. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10-12 mins, or until stock is absorbed. Remove from heat. Add 1/2 the meatballs, currants and pistachios to rice and mix to combine. Let stand, covered, for 10 mins.
Meanwhile, whisk together yogurt and tahini in a small bowl.
Add 2 tbsp cilantro to rice mixture and stir to combine. Serve pilaf topped with remaining meatballs and tahini yogurt. Garnish with remaining cilantro and finely chopped tomato.

title: glazed coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line base and sides of two 10 x 3 inch rimmed baking trays.

Cream butter and beat until pale and creamy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Fold into creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.

Mix 1/3 of batter with coffee until well combined. Distribute 1/2 of remaining plain batter between prepared pans. Spread coffee batter over top. Finish with remaining plain batter. Bake for 45 mins, until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 10 mins then turn out onto a wire rack to cool completely.

Meanwhile, to make the coffee glaze, whisk coffee and powdered sugar until smooth. Stir over a double boiler for 5 mins, until glossy and pourable. Pour over cake. Let stand for 10 mins to set. Slice.

title: chicken caesar burgers
directions: Combine ground chicken, breadcrumbs and parsley in a large bowl. Season to taste. Shape into four patties. Wrap each patty in a slice of bacon. Place on a plate. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 30 mins.
Meanwhile, for the caesar dressing, combine all ingredients in a small bowl. Season to taste.

Heat a large nonstick skillet on medium-low heat. Spray patties with no stick cooking spray. Cook patties for 6-8 mins each side, until browned and cooked through. Place on paper towels. Let stand for 5 mins; cover to keep warm.
Lightly toast cut sides of buns. Drizzle a little caesar dressing over bun bottoms. Top with lettuce, chicken patties, egg, additional caesar dressing and Parmesan cheese, and bun tops. Serve.

title: roast asian pork and greens
directions: For the sauce, mix all ingredients in a small bowl.
Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line a baking dish with parchment paper.
Place pork on prepared dish. Brush liberally with half of the sauce mixture. Bake for 10 mins. Transfer pork to a plate.
Add noodles to dish. Top with bok choy, choy sum leaves, then choy sum stems and white part of green onions.
Stir 2 tbsp water into remaining sauce mixture. Pour over vegetables and noodles in dish. Position pork on top. Bake a further 10 mins.
Let pork stand for 5 mins. Divide noodles and greens among serving bowls. Slice pork and divide among bowls. Spoon over pan juices. Sprinkle with remaining green onion and cilantro.

title: white russian (with foam)
directions: Fill four glasses with ice. Mix together the liqueur and vodka, then pour over the ice.

Pour 1/3 cup milk into a small glass bowl and microwave for 1 min until hot. Remove and whisk until frothy. Divide the remaining cold milk among the glasses and briefly stir. Spoon some hot milk foam over the top of each glass and serve.

title: strawberry banana tempura
directions: To make the dip, place the strawberries in a food processor with the sugar; blend until smooth. Pour into a small dish.
To make the tempura, sift the flour and cinnamon into bowl; make a well in the center. Pour 2/3 cup cold water into the well. Mix to form a batter. Set aside.
Fill a medium saucepan 1/3 of the way with oil. Heat until a cube of bread dropped into the hot oil browns in 30 seconds.

Dip 1/4 of the strawberries and banana slices into the batter to coat. Fry for 2-3 mins until batter is golden. Remove from oil using a slotted spoon. Drain on paper towels, then keep warm in a low oven.
Repeat 3 more times with the remaining strawberries and banana slices.
Serve the fruit tempura on a warmed serving plate dusted with powdered sugar, with fruit dip on the side.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Whisk yolks, mustard and vinegar in a large bowl until thick and pale.
Slowly add oil in a thin, steady stream, whisking constantly, until thick.
Stir in ketchup, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces.

title: stir-fried pork meatballs
directions: Combine pork, 1 tbsp soy sauce and garlic. Shape tablespoons of mixture into balls and chill 20 minutes.
Heat oil in a wok or large frying pan on high. Stir-fry meatballs in 2 batches, 4-5 minutes each batch. Remove and set aside.

Stir-fry bok choy, broccoli and snow peas 1-2 minutes. In a small bowl, combine remaining soy sauce, sugar and sesame oil. Add mixture to wok and toss until bubbling. Add meatballs and orange segments; cook 1-2 minutes.
Sprinkle with chives and serve with rice and sweet chili sauce.

title: harira
directions: In a food processor, puree tomatoes with saffron water and spices until smooth. Season and set aside.

Heat a large Dutch oven over high heat. Add oil and sear meat until browned. Set aside. Add onions and celery to pan and cook over medium heat for 5 mins, or until soft. Add garlic and cook for 1 min. Return meat to pan along with tomato puree. Add lentils, chickpeas and 6 cups water. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 2 hours, or until meat and chickpeas are tender.
Add 2 cups water and return to a simmer. Add spaghetti and cook for 20 mins, or until al dente. Season.
Stir in cilantro, parsley and lemon juice. Season. Serve with lemon wedges and dates on the side.

title: lime blueberry ice cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°F. Separate 2 eggs and beat the whites with a pinch of salt until soft peaks form using an electric hand mixer. Continue beating while adding vanilla extract and 1/4 cup sugar until the mixture is glossy white and the sugar has completely dissolved. Stir in the egg yolks then fold in the flour and cornstarch.

Transfer to a parchment paper lined 10 inch round springform pan and bake for about 12 minutes then remove and allow to cool on a wire rack. When cooled, remove form the cake pan, discard the parchment paper and return the cake to the pan.

To make the filling, separate 4 eggs and beat the whites and a pinch of salt until soft peaks form with an electric hand mixer. Continue beating while gradually adding 2/3 cup sugar, egg yolks and lime zest then carefully fold in the cream cheese and lime juice. In a separate bowl, whip the cream until stiff using an electric hand mixer and fold into the egg mixture. Spread the mixture over the cake, smooth and freeze for at least 6 hours.

For the topping, bring 1/2 cup water and 1/3 cup sugar to a boil and simmer for 2 minutes. Place the frozen blueberries and hot syrup in a blender and puree. Spread over the cake and freeze for another 1 1/2 hours. Allow the cake to thaw for 20 minutes before serving, garnish with a sprig of mint

title: duck liver paté with sweet and sour onions
directions: Rinse the duck livers under cold water and pat dry with paper towels. Trim the duck livers of any connective tissue and cut away any green-stained liver.
Cook the pancetta, onion and garlic in a large frying pan until browned. Add the stock and oregano and cook, stirring, and bring to a boil.
Heat the olive oil in a heavy-based frying pan and cook the duck livers until just firm, but pink on the inside. Season well. Add the vinegar to the pan and cook, stirring, until the liquid boils.

Combine the livers, pancetta and the onion mixture, and the butter in a blender or food processor and process until smooth, than press through a sieve. Puree the mixture again until smooth. Season to taste then cover and refrigerate for several hours.

Meanwhile, to make the sweet and sour onions, heat the oil in a shallow frying pan and add the onion and sugar. Cook over a medium heat, stirring occasionally, for about 15 mins or until the onions are browned lightly and caramelized. Add the wine and vinegar and cook, stirring, until half of the liquid has evaporated. Add the currants and continue to reduce over a medium heat until the liquid coats the back of a spoon. Add the thyme and season to taste. Leave to cool to room temperature.

Next, make the croutons. Preheat the oven to 425°F. Using a serrated knife, cut the crusts squarely off the bread, then cut the bread into logs and finally slice thinly into individual squares of about 1 inch each. If using a baguette, slice thinly. Lay the bread slices on a large baking tray and bake in a 350F oven until browned and crisp. Cool to room temperature.
To serve, place a dollop of the sweet and sour onions on each crouton. Using a teaspoon dipped in hot water, scoop out dainty dollops of pate and nest on top of the onions.

title: chickpea vegetables with cumin couscous
directions: Place chickpeas in medium bowl, cover with cold water; stand overnight, drain. Rinse under cold water; drain. Place chickpeas in medium saucepan of boiling water. Return to the boil, reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 40 mins or until tender. Drain.

Meanwhile, preheat oven to 160°C/140°C fan/gas 3. Heat oil in large deep flameproof baking dish; cook leek and carrot, stirring, until just tender. Add garlic, rosemary and chickpeas; cook, stirring, until fragrant. Add vinegar and stock; bring to the boil. Cover; cook in oven for 30 mins.

Meanwhile, make cumin couscous. Combine the water and couscous in medium heatproof bowl, cover; stand for 5 mins or until liquid is absorbed, fluffing with fork occasionally. Add oil and cumin; toss gently to combine.
Remove dish from oven; stir in spinach, juice, extra oil and extra garlic. Serve chickpea vegetables with couscous and salad.

title: cheesy barbecue baked potatoes
directions: Preheat grill. Wrap potatoes in foil and place on grill for 1 hour, or until a knife inserted into the center comes out easily. Cut off top 1/3 of potatoes and scoop out flesh, leaving a 1/4 inch-thick wall at the bottom. Reserve flesh.

Spread 1 tbsp salsa into each potato. With a fork, mash together potato flesh, green onion, sour cream, butter and cheese. Season then distribute between potatoes. Place on grill over indirect heat, cover and cook for 15 mins, or until hot.

title: seafood mornay
directions: Preheat the broiler to high. Heat bechamel sauce in a saucepan on medium heat. Stir in cheese and lemon juice. Season to taste.
Add fish, shrimp, mussels, scallops, mushroom and onion. Cook, stirring, for 3-5 mins until fish is cooked. Stir in dill.

Spoon evenly into 4 ovenproof gratin dishes. Combine Parmesan cheese and breadcrumbs and sprinkle evenly over each seafood mornay. Broil for 3-5 mins or until golden. Garnish with additional dill and serve with crusty bread.

title: white fish tartare
directions: Combine all ingredients, season then cover and chill for 15 mins. Place a tart ring on each serving plate, fill with tartare and press down lightly. Serve garnished with reserved herbs.

title: apple and pear pies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F.
Combine the sliced fruit with the lemon juice, figs, granulated sugar and cinnamon in a medium bowl. Divide the fruit mixture among four 1-cup shallow baking dishes; cover with foil.
Bake for 10 mins or until the fruit starts to soften. Remove the foil. Top each dish with a scrunched sheet of phyllo. Spray the phyllo with no stick cooking spray.
Bake for 30 mins or until lightly browned. Dust with sifted powdered sugar and serve with ice cream.

title: lamb curry with fragrant rice
directions: Heat the oil in a wok or a large skillet over medium-high heat. Cook the onion for 5 mins, stirring often to prevent browning. Stir in the garlic and cilantro stalks.
When the onion is translucent and slightly golden, add the lamb and cook for 5 mins, stirring, until browned. Stir in the curry paste and cook the mixture for another 1-2 mins, until fragrant.
Add the tomato puree and stock and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat and simmer, uncovered for 25 mins, until the lamb is tender.

Meanwhile make the fragrant rice. Place all the rice ingredients in a microwave-safe container. Microwave, uncovered, on high for 16 mins, until tender. If the rice is not tender, continue to microwave and test every 2 mins. Set aside for 2 mins, then fluff up with a fork to separate the grains.
Spray the popadums with cooking oil spray and place 4 at a time in the microwave on a piece of paper towel. Microwave each batch on high for a minute, until expanded and crisp.
Taste the curry for spiciness. To add more heat, add fresh chili or sambal oelek, to taste.
When ready to serve, stir in spinach and cilantro leaves. Serve the curry with rice, popadums, and tzatziki.

title: lemon sorbet
directions: Stir lemon zest, sugar and 1/2 cup water in a small saucepan over medium heat, without boiling, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Boil, without stirring, for 5 mins, or until syrup thickens slightly. Strain into a heatproof container and let cool to room temperature. Stir in lemon juice then transfer to a loaf pan, cover with foil and freeze for 3 hours, or until almost set.
Blend or process almost frozen sorbet with egg white until smooth. Return to loaf pan, cover and freeze for 3 hours, or overnight.

title: oatmeal sandwich cookies with nutella ganache
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, sugar and eggs. Add melted butter and mix until just combined. Chill for 30 mins.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Line 2 baking trays with parchment paper. Spoon 16 dollops of batter onto each baking tray. Bake for 14 mins. Let cool on tray for 2-3 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.

To make the filling, melt Nutella over a double boiler. Add chopped chocolate and stir until melted. Spread over 16 cookies then sandwich with remaining 16 cookies. Press together lightly. Allow to dry then serve.

title: plum cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°F. Grease and line the base of an 8 inch round spring-form pan. Place the butter, brown sugar and sugar in a bowl and beat together until pale and creamy. Gradually beat in the eggs then add the vanilla extract and lemon zest. Sift over the flour, baking powder and a pinch of salt and fold in with a metal spoon along with 5 tbsp of the cream.

Spoon the mixture into the prepared cake pan and level the surface. Scatter over the plums. Bake for 30 mins then cover the top of the cake pan loosely with foil and bake for a further 20-30 mins until the cake is golden brown and a skewer inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean. Leave to cool in the pan for 20 mins then remove from the pan and cool on a wire rack.
Softly whip the rest of the cream with the egg nog or cream liqueur, if desired. Serve the sliced cake, warm or cold, dusted with powdered sugar and with the whipped cream.

title: banana and blueberry bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease an 8 x 4 inch loaf pan. Line the bottom with parchment paper.
Silt flour, baking powder and cinnamon into a large bowl. Stir in the sugar.
Mix bananas, butter, eggs and vanilla in a medium bowl. Fold into dry ingredients until combined. Stir in blueberries. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 55-60 mins, until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on a wire rack.

title: italian salami and pesto sandwiches
directions: Spread pesto over 2 slices of bread. Top with salami, arugula, peppers and cheese. Season. Sandwich with remaining bread. Serve.

title: berry custard pastries
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F.

Cut 1 puff pastry sheet in 1/2. Sprinkle 1/2 with 1 tsp powdered sugar. Place other 1/2 of puff pastry on top then roll up tightly from the short side. Cut into 8 pieces. Repeat with remaining pastry sheet.
Lay rounds, cut-side up, on a cutting board dusted lightly with extra powdered sugar. Roll each round into an oval.
Arrange ovals on baking trays lined with parchment paper. Bake for 6 mins. Flip over and bake for another 6 mins, or until browned.
Meanwhile, to make the custard cream, whip cream, custard and powdered sugar until thick. Refrigerate for 30 mins, or until firm.

To serve, place a little custard cream on 8 serving plates to prevent pastry from slipping. Place 8 pastry ovals on cream. Divide 1/2 the berries between pastries. Top with custard cream then remaining berries and pastry ovals. Dust with extra powdered sugar.

title: australian style pancakes with ricotta and honey
directions: In a bowl, combine the ricotta, eggs, flour, currants, honey and vanilla.

Heat the oil in a frying pan over a medium heat. Place tablespoon measures of batter into the pan, flattening lightly with a spatula. Cook in batches for 1-2 mins each side, until cooked through and golden. Drain on a paper towel.
Dust with powdered sugar. Serve topped with extra honey and sliced banana, if desired.

title: mars bar cheesecake
directions: Mix cookie crumbs with 5 1/2 tbsp melted butter. Press mixture into base and side of an 8 inch springform pan. Chill.
For the butterscotch sauce, simmer brown sugar, remaining butter and 2 tbsp cream for 6 mins. Set aside.

Meanwhile, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Mix 2 tbsp with bloomed gelatin and heat gently until gelatin melts. Mix back into main mixture. Fold in candy bars. Whip 1 1/2 cups heavy cream to soft peaks then fold in. Transfer 2/3 of mixture to prepared pan. Drizzle 2/3 of butterscotch sauce over top. Swirl into cream cheese mixture. Repeat with remaining cream cheese mixture and butterscotch sauce. Chill for 3 hours, or until set.
For the chocolate sauce, combine chocolate and remaining cream in a small saucepan. Stir over low heat until smooth.
Serve cheesecake drizzled with milk chocolate sauce.

title: ramen noodle cake with sesame veggies
directions: Place noodles and contents of the spice packets in a heatproof bowl. Cover with boiling water. Let stand, covered, 5 minutes, or until noodles are soft. Drain and return to bowl.
Snip noodles into shorter lengths with kitchen scissors. Stir in egg and season.
Preheat the broiler to high. Heat oil in a 9 inch non-stick frying pan.
Add noodle mixture and flatten with a spatula to cover base of pan. Cook 2 minutes. Reduce heat to low and cook a further 8 minutes, or until browned underneath and just set in the center.
Transfer pan to oven and broil for 2 minutes, or until set. Let stand 2 minutes. Turn out noodle cake onto a serving plate.
Wipe pan clean. Place over moderate heat.

Add carrot, pepper and 1 teaspoon sesame oil and cook, stirring, 1 minute, or until just soft. Remove from heat. Add green onions, sprouts, cilantro, remaining sesame oil and fish sauce and toss to combine.
Top noodle cake with vegetable mixture and sprinkle with sesame seeds. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: spiced potato and chicken soup
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan on medium-high heat. Cook the chicken for 4-5 mins until golden. Remove from the pan.
Add onion, garlic, spices and potatoes to the pan. Cook, stirring, for 3 mins.
Return chicken to pan and add stock and milk. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 15 mins until potatoes are tender. Stir in cilantro and season with salt and black pepper.

title: ham, lemon and parsley pasta
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water according to package directions.

Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Add the garlic and chili pepper and cook about 3 mins or until softened. Add the ham and cook about 2 mins or until heated through. Remove from the heat.
Drain pasta and add to the skillet with the lemon peel and parsley; toss to coat well. Season with salt and pepper. Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate eclairs with white chocolate cream
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Line a baking pan with parchment paper.

For the choux pastry, place butter, 1/2 cup water, milk, granulated sugar and salt in medium saucepan on medium-high heat. Bring to a simmer. Stir until sugar has dissolved. Stir in flour and cook for 30 secs until dough comes cleanly away from sides of pan.

Remove from heat. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Spoon into piping bag fitted with a 3/4-inch plain tip. Pipe dough onto prepared pan to form eclairs, about 4 inches long and 1 inch wide, leaving room for spreading.
Bake for 30 mins or until puffed and golden. Turn oven off and keep door ajar. Cool pastry in oven for 30 mins. Transfer to rack to cool completely.
For the white chocolate cream, place 2/3 cup of the heavy cream, liqueur and vanilla bean in small saucepan on medium-high heat. Bring to a simmer.
Place white chocolate in a large bowl and add hot cream. Let stand for 15 secs, then whisk to combine. Refrigerate until cold.
Using knife, prick small hole in one end of each pastry. This is where you will pipe in the cream.
Beat remaining 1 cup heavy cream and white chocolate cream with electric mixer until firm peaks form. Spoon into piping bag fitted with 1/5-inch tip. Carefully pipe cream into eclairs.

For the glaze, place bittersweet chocolate, powdered sugar and butter in heatproof bowl and place over pan of gently simmering water to melt. Stir to combine. Remove from heat. Dip top of each pastry into melted chocolate and return to wire rack to set.

title: blueberry and yogurt pastries
directions: Place a quarter of the yogurt in a strainer lined with a clean damp piece of cheese cloth. Place over a bowl. Sprinkle yogurt with a little of the brown sugar. Top with another quarter of the yogurt, then a little more brown sugar. Repeat twice more, finishing with brown sugar. Cover with plastic wrap. Chill overnight until yogurt is very thick and all liquid has drained away into bowl.

Spread pistachios over a large greased baking tray. Combine sugar and a 1/4 cup of water in a small saucepan over moderate heat. Cook and stir until sugar dissolves, then simmer, without stirring, for 3-4 minutes or until golden. Carefully pour hot syrup over pistachios, tilting baking tray to cover. Stand until set and cooled. Process in a food processor until fine crumbs form.

Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a large baking tray with parchment paper. Working with one sheet at a time, brush phyllo with melted butter and sprinkle with a little of the pistachio crumbs. Repeat layers with phyllo and crumbs, finishing with a layer of pistachio crumbs. Transfer stack to prepared tray. Bake for 8-10 minutes or until golden and crisp. Using a large serrated knife, cut filo stack into 8 equal pieces lengthwise. Half crosswise to form 16 pieces in total. Cool.
To serve, place 1 piece on a serving plate. Top with some yoghurt and blueberries. Repeat the layer once more.

title: nut and seed bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Grease and line 2 - 7x3 inch loaf pans with parchment paper.

Place flour in a bowl. Cut in butter until mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Add seeds, figs and 1/2 cup pecans. Add yogurt and egg. Mix until just combine. Divide between prepared pans, smooth surface and sprinkle with remaining pecans. Bake for 35 mins, or until loaves are golden. Let cool in pan for 2 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Serve sliced, with butter and honey.

title: jam and cream sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease 2 - 8 inch cake pans. Line bases with parchment paper.

Whisk eggs for 5 mins, or until thick and pale. Gradually add sugar, beating well after each addition until sugar dissolves. Beat in vanilla. Sift flour over top then fold in until just combined. Distribute between prepared pans. Bake for 18-20 mins, or until golden and spring back when touched lightly. Let cool in pans for 5 mins then turn out onto wire racks to cool completely.
To assemble, place 1 cake on a large cake stand. Spread jam over top then whipped cream. Top with remaining cake.

Sift powdered sugar into a heatproof bowl. Add butter and 2 tbsp boiling water and stir until smooth. Tint with food coloring. Spread icing over cake, letting it drizzle over sides. Let set before serving.

title: spicy tex-mex vegetable soup
directions: Heat the oil in a large pan and saute the onions and garlic for 5 mins. Add the mushrooms and tomatoes and saute 3-4 mins then stir in the chili spice mix and cook for 1 more min. Pour in 4 cups of water and add the tomato puree, sliced peppers, corn and all but a few of the spring onions. Simmer for 10 mins, stirring occasionally. Season to taste with sugar, salt and freshly ground black pepper. Serve in warmed bowls topped with the reserved spring onions, grated cheese, sour cream, tortilla chips and a sprinkling of cayenne pepper. Add a whole pickled jalapeno to each bowl, if using.

title: bacon cornbread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. To make the batter, mix the cornmeal, flour, baking powder, sugar and red pepper in a bowl and season. Melt the butter in a saucepan, then mix with the buttermilk and eggs. Pour into the dry ingredients and mix until smooth.

Fry the bacon in a dry frying pan for 3-4 mins, stirring. Add the onion and corn and saute for 2-3 mins. Mix into the batter then pour into a greased 10 inch springform cake pan. Sprinkle with parsley and bake for 20-25 mins. Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: crab salad canapés
directions: In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise, chives, parsley, mustard, seasoning mix, 1/2 tsp lime zest and 2 tbsp lime juice. Season. Place a heaping teaspoon on each cucumber slice. Garnish with parsley leaves.

title: fettuccine with chicken, fennel and lemon
directions: Cook pasta in a large saucepan of boiling, salted water according to package directions. Drain.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a large skillet on high heat. Cook chicken for 8 mins, until browned and cooked through. Remove from pan.
Cook fennel for 6 mins, until tender. Return chicken to pan with wine; bring to a boil. Stir in cream, lemon peel and juice, and capers. Add pasta; toss to combine.

title: mustard glazed roast beef with gravy
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Place beef in roasting pan. Spread mustard over surface of meat and season with salt and pepper. Drizzle with oil and roast for 45 mins. spoon pan juices over meat and roast for a further 15 mins (for rare) to 30 mins (for medium). Remove from oven, transfer beef to warm platter and wrap loosely in foil. Set aside to rest.

To make gravy, melt butter in a saucepan and saute onions, garlic and thyme with a little salt and pepper over medium heat for 20 mins until browned. Add port or red wine, cook for 1 minute, then remove from heat. Place roasting pan with meat juices on stove top over low heat. Stir in flour with wooden spoon and cook, stirring and scraping bottom of tin, for 30 seconds. Stir in water, bring to boil and then stir in onion and port mixture. Simmer over medium heat for 10 mins, strain through sieve into serving pitcher and keep warm until ready to serve.
Carve beef and serve with gravy and vegetables of choice.

title: cheesy sweet potato and chive muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly spray a 12-cup muffin pan with no stick cooking spray.
Sift flour into a large bowl. Stir in sweet potato and 1 tbsp of the chives.
Mix buttermilk, butter and egg in a medium bowl. Season to taste. Add to the flour mixture. Mix lightly until just combined. Do not over-mix.
Spoon batter into muffin cups, filling 2/3 full. Press a cube of cheese into each. Sprinkle with remaining 1 tbsp chives.
Bake for 25-30 mins until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Serve muffins warm.

title: warm beef, noodle and bok choy salad
directions: Cover noodles with cold water in a large bowl. Let stand for 5 mins. Heat a grill pan on high heat or preheat the grill to medium-high. Lightly brush steak with oil. Grill for 3-4 mins each side, or until cooked to desired doneness. Transfer to a platter. Let stand, loosely covered with foil, for 5 mins.
For the dressing, combine chili pepper, lime juice, fish sauce and 1/4 cup water in a small bowl. Add sugar to taste. Set aside.

Cook bok choy in saucepan of boiling salted water for 2 mins, until tender but still crisp. Remove and drain. Drain noodles and add to hot water in saucepan. Remove from heat and set aside for 3 mins. Drain thoroughly.
Cut steak across grain into thin slices. Toss noodles with dressing, bok choy, cilantro and beef. Serve with lime slices.

title: gazpacho
directions: Place garlic, onion and salt in a small saucepan; cover with cold water. Bring to a boil on high heat. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, 20 mins, or until tender. Cool to room temperature; drain.

Meanwhile, preheat the oven to 425°F. Rub peppers with 1 tbsp of the oil. Place peppers on baking pan. Roast 30 mins, or until blistered and blackened, turning occasionally. Transfer peppers to a bowl. Cover with plastic wrap; let stand until cooled. Peel skin from peppers and discard seeds. Reserve any pepper juices.

Place cucumber, tomatoes, chili pepper, basil, peppers with all the juices, and boiled onion and garlic in a blender. Blend on high speed until smooth. Add remaining oil and wine; blend until just combined.

Strain pepper mixture through a fine sieve over a large bowl. Season to taste with salt, pepper and sugar. Refrigerate at least 3 hours, before serving. To serve, pour gazpacho into individual cups or glasses.

title: fruit salad with citrus sugar
directions: To make the citrus sugar, mix the fruit zests with the sugar and mint until well combined.
Just before serving, layer the cut fruit on a large serving platter, sprinkling the citrus sugar between layers.
Serve with extra mint leaves as garnish.

title: sun-dried tomato and pepper tapenade
directions: In a food processor, combine peppers, tomatoes, tomato oil, garlic, pine nuts and lemon juice. Process until almost smooth. Season.
Blanch green beans in boiling, salted water for 1 min, or until tender. Drain. Toss with tapenade, feta and hot pasta. Serve with mixed greens.

title: mediterranean sausage tart
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Grease a 9-inch round tart pan with removable bottom. Place pan on a baking pan. Line prepared pan with pastry; trim excess. Line pastry with parchment paper; cover bottom with dried beans, rice or pie weights. Bake pastry for 10 mins. Remove weights and paper; bake pastry for 5 mins more or until lightly browned.

Meanwhile, heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Add onion, zucchini and pepper; cook and stir for 4-5 mins or until browned. Remove from pan. Add sausages; cook and turn for 6 mins or until browned all over.
Arrange vegetables, tomato and sausages in tart crust. Whisk eggs and cream in a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Pour egg mixture into tart crust.
Bake for 25-30 mins or until set and golden brown. Serve with salad.

title: puff pastry
directions: In a food processor, pulse flour, melted butter, 1 tsp salt and 1 cup ice water until combined and starting to come together. Transfer to a lightly floured work surface and knead briefly until dough is smooth. Cut a cross in the top and wrap in plastic wrap. Chill for 30 mins.
Meanwhile, place cold butter between 2 sheets baking paper. Hit with a rolling pin until flattened and forms a 5 inch square, 2/3 inch thick. Chill until required.

Remove dough from refrigerator and place on a lightly floured work surface. Press rolling pin into 1 corner of dough and roll out into a "petal." Turn the dough 90° and repeat. Repeat twice more until you achieve a rough cross shape, with a slight lump in the center.
Place chilled butter in center of cross. Fold petals over butter to enclose. Lightly tap pastry with a rolling pin to seal edges and flatten the square a little.

Roll out to form a long 10x22 inch rectangle, keeping edges straight. Fold bottom quarter of pastry up towards the center, taking care to align edges. Brush off excess flour. Fold top quarter down to the center. Fold top half over bottom half to make a neat rectangle. Brush off excess flour.

Turn the dough 90° to the right (so the seam is facing your right hand side). Roll out into a long rectangle. Fold into thirds (like a business letter) then roll out to form another rectangle. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill for 30 mins.

Roll out into a long rectangle and repeat Steps 5 and 6 twice more. Wrap and chill for 10 mins before rolling and shaping for baking. Pastry can be kept chilled for 2 days or frozen for several months.

title: mediterranean lamb stew
directions: Heat oil in a pan and sear lamb on all sides. Remove from pan and set aside. Add onion, garlic and chili, and saute. Add flour and cook briefly. Deglaze with white wine, stock and vinegar. Add lamb, tomato paste, bay leaf and rosemary. Simmer for 40-45 mins.
About 1 min before end of cooking, add tomatoes and olives. Season with salt, pepper and eggplant chutney. Serve stew with pita bread

title: stir-fried noodles with asparagus and tempeh
directions: Cook noodles in boiling salted water until al dente. Drain and rinse under cold running water to cool. Spread out on a clean tea towel for at least 1 hour, until dry.

Heat 1 tsp oil in wok or large frying pan. Cook tempeh for 2 mins per side, until golden brown. Set aside. Add remaining oil to wok. Stir-fry asparagus, garlic, ginger and green onions over high heat for 2-3 mins, until bright green. Set aside.

Add noodles to wok and stir-fry over high heat for 4 mins, until noodles separate and dry out slightly. Add bean sprouts and cook for 2 mins. Add oyster sauce, sesame oil and 1/4 cup water. Return asparagus and tempeh to wok and toss to combine. Serve with cilantro.

title: chocolate ice cream with apricots and raspberry sauce
directions: Combine the sugar, chile pepper and half the raspberries in a saucepan. Simmer over medium heat, stirring, for 2 mins. Remove from the heat and cool. Stir in the remaining raspberries.
Divide the ice cream and apricots among four dessert dishes. Drizzle the raspberry sauce over the apricots and serve.

title: calves liver with roasted onions and apples
directions: Heat 1 tbsp of oil in a frying pan and cook the bacon until crisp, remove and drain on paper towels reserving the bacon fat in the pan. Saute the apple rings in the hot bacon fat 2 mins each side. Remove and keep warm. Coat the onion rings with 2 tbsp of flour and fry them in the hot fat until crisp. Remove and drain on paper towels.

Coat the liver in 4 tbsp of flour. Heat 2 tbsp of oil in a frying pan and saute the liver for about 6 mins, turning as necessary. Serve the liver, apple slices, onion rings and bacon garnished with parsley with mashed potatoes on the side.

title: ham, spinach and jalapeño pizzas
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.
Heat the oil in a frying pan. Add the spinach and cook for three minutes or until soft, turning occasionally.
Drain the spinach, then divide between pizza crusts, spreading evenly. Top with ham and mozzarella and sprinkle with the jalapenos.
Place on prepared baking sheets and bake for 15 minutes or until cheese is golden brown.

title: crispy red snapper with potato salad
directions: Brush fish with oil and season to taste. Cover and chill until needed.

For the potato salad, place potatoes in a saucepan of salted water. Bring to a boil and cook for 8-10 mins until just tender. Drain well and cool slightly. In a large bowl, combine potatoes, onion, parsley and capers.
For the dressing, whisk together the sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice. Season to taste. Drizzle dressing over potato salad and toss gently.

Heat a large frying pan on high. Cook fish, skin-side down, for 4-5 min,s until crisp and golden. Flip and cook 1-2 more mins until flesh flakes, when tested with a fork. Serve with potato salad, arugula and lemon wedges.

title: peach yogurt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease and line an 8x4 inch loaf pan with parchment paper. Pour melted margarine into pan. Arrange peaches over top.

Cream remaining spread, sugar and orange zest until light and fluffy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well between additions. Add yogurt. Fold in semolina, ground almonds and baking powder. Transfer to prepared pan, smooth surface and bake for 50-55 mins, or until a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 5 mins then transfer to a wire rack to cool.
Serve in slices.

title: easy onion and arugula pappardelle
directions: Cook pasta in a large saucepan of boiling, salted water according to package directions; drain well. Return to pan.
Meanwhile, heat oil in large skillet on medium heat. Cook onion, stirring, 10-15 mins, until caramelized. Add olives, arugula and lemon juice. Toss well; season to taste.
Add onion mixture to pasta; toss well. Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.

title: spicy green tomato relish
directions: Combine the vegetables in a large bowl. Sprinkle with the salt; cover. Let stand for several hours. Rinse under cold water; drain well.

Combine the vegetables, vinegars and spices in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally, for about 45 mins. Add the sugar and stir, without boiling, until the sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil and boil, uncovered, for 15 mins.
Pour into hot sterilized jars; seal immediately. Label and date jars when cold. Store in a cool dry place. Once opened, store in the refrigerator.

title: caramelized carrots
directions: Heat the butter and oil in large frying pan, then add the carrots and cook, covered, until just tender.
Add the sugar and cook, stirring, for about 10 mins or until the carrots caramelize. Stir in the parsley and vinegar and serve.

title: herb omelet with sautéed mushrooms
directions: Combine herbs in a small bowl.

Heat 1 tbsp each of the butter and oil in a large skillet on high heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring, 5 mins. Stir in 2 tbsp of the water; cook until water evaporates and mushrooms are tender. Transfer mushrooms to a bowl. Stir in lemon peel and juice and 2 tbsp of the herb mixture. Cover to keep warm.
Gently whisk eggs and 1/3 cup water in a large bowl. Whisk in remaining herb mixture.

Heat 1/2 tbsp of the remaining butter and 1 tsp of the remaining oil in a medium skillet on medium heat. When butter mixture bubbles, pour a quarter of the egg mixture into pan. Cook, tilting pan, until egg is almost set. Tilt pan backwards and fold omelet in half. Cook 30 seconds then slide onto serving plate. Repeat, wiping out pan before each addition to make a total of four omelets.
Serve omelets topped with sauteed mushrooms.

title: barbecue pork spare ribs
directions: Combine tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and sugar in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil then remove from heat and let cool for 10 mins.
Place pork in a large shallow baking dish. Pour marinade over pork, cover and chill for 3 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain pork, reserving marinade. Cook on a heated, oiled grill for about 30 mins, or until cooked through, turning and brushing frequently with reserved marinade.
Boil remaining marinade in a small saucepan for 5 mins, or until thickened slightly. Slice spare ribs into portions and serve with hot marinade.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine vanilla bean pods, vanilla bean seeds, milk and cream. Bring just to a boil then remove from heat.

Meanwhile, whisk together egg yolks and sugar in a large bowl until creamy. Gradually whisk in hot milk mixture. Transfer entire mixture to saucepan and stir over low heat, without boiling, until custard thickens slightly.
Strain custard into a large measuring cup or bowl and press plastic wrap directly over surface of custard. Let cool then refrigerate for 1 hour, or until cold.
Pour custard into an ice cream maker and churn according to manufacturer's instructions.

If you do not have an ice cream maker, transfer mixture to a shallow cake pan, cover with foil and freeze until almost firm. Transfer ice cream to a large bowl and chop coarsely. Beat with an electric mixer until smooth then pour back into cake pan and freeze until firm. Repeat twice more.

title: low fat vegetable soup
directions: Heat the oil in a large saucepan on medium heat. Add the onions and garlic and saute for 3-4 mins. Add the chopped vegetables, except for the tomatoes and green beans. Add enough water to just cover the vegetables. Bring to a boil. Stir in the granulated vegetable bouillon. Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 mins.

Remove 2/3 of vegetables from the soup. Puree the remaining vegetables in the pan with an immersion blender. Return the chopped vegetables to the soup. Add the tomatoes and green beans. Bring to a simmer. Garnish with chopped fresh basil leaves.

title: duck in crispy wonton cups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease 2 (12-cup) mini muffin pans.
Press wonton wrappers into recesses and lightly coat with oil. Bake for 8 mins, or until golden brown. Remove from muffin pans and let cool.
Arrange sliced duck on a baking tray, cover with foil and bake for 10 mins.
Whisk together hoisin sauce and soy sauce in a medium bowl. Add duck, cilantro and chopped spring onions and mix to combine. Spoon into wonton cases and top with thinly sliced spring onions.

title: spaghetti with meatballs
directions: Combine the ground beef, breadcrumbs, egg, half the sage and half the rosemary in a large bowl. Season and roll tablespoons of mixture into balls. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large frying pan on medium. Cook meatballs for 6 mins, or until browned all over and cooked through. Drain on paper towels.

Heat remaining oil in a large saucepan on medium. Saute onion and garlic for 3 mins, until soft. Add tomato puree, remaining herbs and 1 2/3 cups water. Bring to a boil. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 mins. Season to taste, add meatballs and simmer for 5 mins.
Meanwhile, prepare spaghetti according to package instructions. Drain. Top with meatballs and garnish with basil.

title: salsa stuffed salmon
directions: To make the salsa, mix the tomatoes, onion, garlic, chili, lime juice, olive oil and cilantro together and season. Place one salmon fillet on a board, spread half of the salsa over the salmon and top with the second fillet. Press down.
Place the egg and breadcrumbs in separate large, flat, shallow dishes. Cut salmon in half then carefully coat all over in egg then breadcrumbs. Cut into 8 (11/4 inch) thick pieces.

Heat oil for shallow frying in a large pan and cook salmon for 15 minutes, carefully turning halfway through cooking, until crisp, golden and cooked through. Serve hot with remaining salsa, spinach and lemon wedges.

title: breakfast bowl
directions: Place watermelon, 1/2 banana, raspberries and 4 ice cubes in a blender. Blend on high speed for about 1 min, or until smooth. Spoon into serving bowls.
Top with remaining banana, fresh berries and muesli. Drizzle with honey and serve immediately.

title: potato and fish stew
directions: Heat the oil in a frying pan, add the onion and saute for 3-4 mins, stirring. Add the potatoes and carrots and saute for 1-2 mins. Sprinkle the flour over the vegetables and saute for another 1-2 mins then mix in the stock. Cover and simmer for 12-15 mins, stirring occasionally.

Mix the fish and lemon juice together and season. Stir the cream and horseradish into the vegetables and bring to a boil. Lower the fish into the sauce and gently simmer for 4-5 mins until cooked through. Serve.

title: white chocolate eggnog
directions: Bring milk to a boil in medium saucepan. Remove from heat.

Meanwhile, whisk egg yolks and sugar in medium bowl until combined. Gradually whisk in hot milk. Return eggnog mixture to pan; stir on low heat, without boiling, until mixture is thick enough to coat the back of a spoon. Remove from heat.
Add the white chocolate, brandy and rum; stir until smooth.
Beat cream in medium bowl with electric mixer until soft peaks form. Pour eggnog into 8 warmed heatproof 3/4-cup serving glasses; top with whipped cream. Serve sprinkled with nutmeg.

title: spiced barbecued turkey with peach and cranberry chutney
directions: Using a mortar and pestle, grind peppercorns, star anise, coriander, cumin and salt until crushed coarsely. Transfer to a large frying pan along with remaining spices. Dry toast until fragrant. Remove from heat and stir in oil. Rub spice mixture over turkey.

Preheat grill. Place turkey, skin-side up, in a deep disposable baking dish. Grill over indirect heat with lid closed for about 2 hours. Remove from grill and cover loosely with foil. Set aside to rest for 10 mins.

Meanwhile, to make the peach and cranberry chutney, place peaches in a large bowl. Cover with boiling water for 30 seconds then drain. Peel away skin and remove pits. Chop peach flesh coarsely. Transfer to a medium saucepan along with remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 1 hour 15 mins, or until thickened.
Serve turkey with chutney.

title: chocolate panna cotta
directions: Lightly grease 2 - 3.5 oz ramekins. Arrange on a baking tray. Gently heat cream, milk, chocolate and sugar over low heat until melted and smooth. Whisk gelatin with 1 tbsp boiling water until dissolved, let cool slightly then add to cream mixture. Distribute between ramekins, cover and chill for 3 hours to overnight, until set. Decorate with chocolate hearts and strawberries.

title: mediterranean lemon lamb stew
directions: Toss the lamb cubes with the flour. Heat the oil in a pan and saute the meat until browned all over. Season with salt and pepper. Add the onion and saute briefly. Stir in the stock and wine, bring to a boil and simmer for about 1 hour. Halve the lemon, squeeze the juice from one half and thinly slice the other. About 20 mins before the end of cooking, add the spinach and lemon slices to the stew.

Whisk the egg yolks with the lemon juice. Remove the pan from the heat. Mix the egg yolk with 1-2 tbsp of the sauce from the pan, then add to the stew, stirring constantly. Season with salt, pepper and nutmeg. Serve with pita bread, if desired.

title: hungarian cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Grease a baking dish. Cook the potatoes in boiling salted water for 5-10 mins then drain and set aside.
Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large saucepan and saute the salami. Add the onions and peppers, briefly saute then add the sauerkraut and cook for about 10 mins.

Meanwhile, mix together the sour cream and eggs and season. Mix the potatoes with the sauerkraut mixture, transfer 1/2 to the prepared dish and top with 1/2 the cream mixture. Repeat then top with feta. Bake for 40-45 mins.

title: stir-fried beef with pepper and black bean sauce
directions: Combine rice wine, soy sauce and cornstarch in a medium bowl. Add beef; turn to coat. Season with pepper and set aside for 10 mins. In a separate bowl, combine black beans, garlic and ginger.
Heat 1 tbsp of the oil in a wok on high heat. Stir-fry half the beef for 3 mins, or until browned. Remove from wok. Repeat with remaining beef.

Heat remaining 2 tbsp oil in wok on high heat. Stir-fry onion for 2 mins. Add black bean mixture and cook for 1 min. Add peppers and stir-fry for 1 min. Return beef to wok with 2 tbsp water and stir-fry for 2 mins, or until heated through. Serve with steamed rice.

title: pork chops with bacon, brussels sprouts and peas
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. In a small bowl, combine fennel seeds, dill and oil. Rub over pork to coat. Season.

Heat a large nonstick frying pan over high heat. Sear pork until browned on both sides. Transfer to a roasting pan and bake for 5 mins, or until just cooked through. Remove from oven, cover with foil and let rest for 10 mins.

Meanwhile, add bacon to frying pan and cook, stirring, until browned. Add peas and cook for 1 min. Add Brussels sprouts and cook, stirring, over high heat until softened slightly. Season. Serve with pork chops.

title: lemon tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Place tart shells, with foil liners still attached, on prepared tray. Whisk 2 tbsp lemon juice, sugar and eggs together until sugar dissolves. Strain then distribute between tart shells. Sprinkle tops with lemon zest and bake for 20 mins, or until filling is just set. Let cool for 5 mins then remove from foil liners. Serve warm, topped with whipped cream.

title: vanilla rum raisin danishes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Lightly grease a large baking sheet.
Heat the brandy in a small saucepan over medium heat. Add the raisins and stir to combine. Remove from heat and allow to cool.

In a small saucepan, heat the milk and vanilla over low heat and slowly bring to a simmer. In a medium bowl, whisk the egg yolks, sugar and flour until creamy and pale. Gradually whisk the hot milk mixture into the egg yolk mixture, then return to pan. Add the butter and cook, stirring, until the mixture boils and thickens. Transfer the custard to a heatproof bowl. Cover the surface directly with plastic wrap to prevent a skin from forming. Allow to cool.

Cut each pastry sheet into 4 squares. Place 2 tablespoons of custard on one half of each pastry square. Top with 2 teaspoons of raisins. Fold the pastry over to enclose the filling and press the edges to seal. Cut 3 long slits in the top to let the steam escape. Bake for 20 mins or until browned. Brush the hot danishes with apricot preserves. Serve.

title: broccoli fritters with radish salad
directions: To make the radish salad: Mix the mustard, vinegar and olive oil. Mix in the capers, radish and onion. Set aside.

To make the fritters: Blanch the broccoli in boiling, salted water for 1-2 mins then drain and rise with cold water. Chop half of it roughly, then place all of the broccoli in a bowl and mix in the flour, eggs and ground almonds. Season with salt and pepper. Heat 3 tbsp of the sunflower oil in a non-stick frying pan. Form the broccoli mixture into 12 fritters. Fry them in batches for 6-8 mins, turning, and adding more oil if necessary. Serve the fritters on 4 plates with the radish salad.

title: baked apples with berries
directions: Place the berries in a fine sieve set over a small bowl, and cover. Thaw in the refrigerator overnight.
Preheat the oven to 325°F.

Core the unpeeled apples about three-quarters of the way down from the stem end, making a hole 1 1/2 inches in diameter. Use a small sharp knife to score around the center of each apple. Make a small deep cut in the bottom of each apple and insert one cardamom pod into each cut.
Pack three-quarters of the berries firmly into the apples and place the apples in a small baking dish. Bake, uncovered, for 45 mins or until the apples are just tender.
Meanwhile, mash the remaining berries with a fork in a small bowl. Stir in the yogurt and honey.
Serve the apples with the yogurt mixture.

title: fresh spaghetti with lemon and chili
directions: Sift flour and salt into bowl. Make well in center and add eggs. Stir until firm dough forms. Knead for 8-10 mins until smooth. Cover in plastic wrap. Chill for 30 mins.
Halve dough and lightly dust with flour. Roll through a pasta machine on widest setting (or with rolling pin). Fold in pasta. Feed through again. Repeat and dust with flour.
Continue rolling, reducing the thickness setting each time until pasta is rolled through the last setting on the machine (or until 1 mm thick). Cut into 4 sheets.
Dust sheets with flour. Feed through a cutter attachment to cut into spaghetti. Drape over a broom handle to dry slightly.
Bring large saucepan of salted water to a boil. Add pasta, stir once, and cook for 2-3 mins until al dente. Drain, reserving 1/4 cup of cooking liquid.
Heat oil in deep frying pan. Saute garlic and chili 30 seconds. Add pasta and toss with cheese, parsley, lemon zest and juice. Season. Serve with a drizzle of oil.

title: spiced chocolate apple cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a 10 inch springform cake pan. Melt the chocolate in a bowl set over a saucepan of simmering water. Leave to cool. Make fan cuts lengthwise in the apple quarters and drizzle with lemon juice.

Cream the butter, salt, sugar and vanilla extract, beat in the eggs one at a time. Sift together the four, baking powder and cocoa. Add to the bowl alternating with the cream. Add the chocolate, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour batter into the cake pan and smooth the surface with a spatula.
Press the apple fans into the surface of the cake batter and bake the cake for about 45 mins or until a skewer inserted into the cake comes out clean. Leave cake to cool.
Heat the jam with a little water in a small saucepan, strain through a sieve. Release the cake from the pan and brush the glaze over the apples.

title: high-fiber mixed berry yogurt smoothies
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth. Pour into 2 glasses.

title: thai chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
In a bowl, combine coconut milk, cilantro, lemongrass, ginger, lime juice, chilies and fish sauce. Add chicken and toss to coat.
Arrange chicken on a baking tray lined with parchment paper. Bake for 10-15 mins, until cooked through. Serve with rice, lime wedges and steamed baby bok choy.

title: potato, bacon, and celery root pie
directions: In a bowl, knead the butter, 1 cup plus 1 tbsp flour, a pinch of salt and 3-4 tbsp cold water to a smooth dough. Shape into a ball, wrap in cling film and chill for 30 mins.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Heat the oil in a skillet and saute the onion for 5 mins, until softened. Add the bacon, sprinkle with 1 tbsp flour and stir. Spoon into an 8-inch round pie dish, add the potatoes and celeriac and mix well. Season with salt and black pepper. Mix the cider and mustard together and pour over the pie filling.

On a lightly floured work surface, roll out the dough to an 8 1/2 inch diameter circle. Lay over the filling, pressing around the edges. Brush with the egg yolk. Bake for 1 hour 15 mins, covering with kitchen foil halfway through cooking if the crust is browning too quickly.

title: haloumi with pomegranate and basil
directions: Heat a large nonstick skillet or grill pan on high heat. Cook the haloumi for 1-2 mins each side, or until golden.
Place the haloumi on a platter. Sprinkle with the pomegranate seeds (the easiest way to do this is to hold the pomegranate half over the platter and hit the rind with a wooden spoon).
Drizzle with lemon juice and olive oil and sprinkle with basil and black pepper. Serve with crusty bread.

title: mohinga noodle and fish soup
directions: Combine tamarind pulp with 1/2 cup of hot water in a small bowl and let stand for 5 minutes. Strain by pressing on the solids. Reserve the tamarind liquid.

Preheat oven to 350°F. Wrap shrimp paste in foil and roast until fragrant, about 5-10 minutes. Combine shrimp paste, snapper, ginger, garlic and 10 cups of water in a large saucepan and bring to a boil, skimming scum that forms on the surface. Reduce heat to medium and simmer until fish is cooked through, about 5-10 minutes. Remove fish from stock and set aside until cool enough to handle, then coarsely shred flesh and discard skin and reserve the bones. Refrigerate until required.

Return fish bones to stock and simmer over low heat until reduced to 4 cups, this will take about 3 hours. Strain stock into a clean saucepan (discard bones) and season to taste with fish sauce and tamarind liquid. Set aside.
Meanwhile, to make the chili oil, stir oil and chili flakes in a small saucepan over medium heat until fragrant, about 2-3 minutes. Set aside.
Stir chickpea flour in a large pan over medium heat until fragrant and lightly toasted, about 1 minute. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.
Heat garlic oil in a non-stick pan over high heat, add turmeric and reserved fish and stir occasionally until golden and crisp, about 10-15 minutes. Set aside and keep warm.

Season warm serving bowls with a little extra garlic oil to taste. Cook noodles in boiling water until just tender, about 3-4 minutes, drain well and divide among bowls. Top noodles with fish, sprinkle with toasted chickpea flour, scatter with cilantro and pour hot stock over. Serve hot with lime wedges and chili oil.

title: spinach and ricotta dumplings
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 10-15 mins until tender. Drain; mash. Cool slightly. Cook spinach in a saucepan with 3 tbsp cold water until wilted. Drain; squeeze out excess liquid. Cool. Add ricotta, flour and yolk to potatoes. Add nutmeg and season. Stir in spinach.

For the tomato sauce, heat oil in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Cook tomatoes and garlic for 4-5 mins, stirring, until soft. Add pesto; stir. Cover; simmer for 3 mins until thick and pulpy. Season. Cover and keep warm.

Using floured hands, shape potato mixture into 3/4-inch dumplings. Cook in boiling water, in 2 batches, for 2-3 mins until dumplings rise to surface. Drain; toss in sauce. Serve with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.

title: baby spinach carbonara
directions: Cook tagliatelle in boiling salted water until al dente. Drain.
Meanwhile, whisk together egg yolks, heavy cream and Parmesan. Set aside.
Heat oil in a large pan. Add pancetta and cook for 2-3 mins. Add tagliatelle and spinach. Toss until spinach is just wilted. Add egg mixture and toss to coat.
Serve immediately sprinkled with extra Parmesan cheese, a grinding of black pepper and crusty bread.

title: trout with shiitake mushrooms
directions: Crush the beans in a small bowl. Add the garlic, ginger, red pepper flakes, and 1/2 each of the soy sauce and the onion; stir to combine.

Place each fish on an oiled piece of foil large enough to completely enclose it. Place 1/4 of the bean mixture inside each fish; wrap tightly in foil. Cook the fish on a heated oiled grill pan, uncovered, for about 10 mins or until cooked to desired doneness.
Meanwhile, cook the mushrooms in a heated oiled large skillet, uncovered, until tender. Drizzle with the remaining soy sauce.
Serve the mushrooms with the fish. Drizzle with the lemon juice and sprinkle with the remaining onion.

title: white chocolate and turkish delight truffles
directions: Combine chocolate and cream in small saucepan over low heat. Stir for 3 mins, or until chocolate is just melted. Transfer to a heatproof bowl and let cool for 15 mins.
Add nougat, Turkish delight and rosewater. Chill for 2 hours, or until firm.
Roll into balls, each around 2 tsp. Place on a parchment paper-lined baking tray and chill for 1 hour, or until firm.
Working in batches of 12, coat balls, 1 at a time, in melted chocolate. Return to tray. Sprinkle with 1 tsp pink sugar. Chill until set. Serve.

title: strawberry crêpes
directions: Toss strawberries with orange juice and powdered sugar. Set aside to macerate for 5 mins.

Heat crepes according to package instructions. Fold in 1/2 twice to form a triangle. Transfer to serving plates. Top with macerated strawberries and ice cream. Drizzle strawberry liquid over top and dust with powdered sugar.

title: sticky pulled pork sandwiches
directions: Score skin and underside of pork at 1/2 inch intervals, to 1/2 inch depth.
In a small bowl, combine spices. Rub evenly over pork to coat. Season to taste. Cover and chill for at least 30 minutes.
Heat oil in a medium, heavy-based saucepan on high. Saute onion 1-2 minutes. Add pork skin side down, and cook 3-4 minutes. Turn and cook 2-3 minutes, until browned all over. Remove.
Add water, barbecue sauce, vinegar and sugar to same saucepan. stirring to dissolve sugar. Bring to a boil. reduce heat to low. Return pork to pan, turning to coat in sauce.

Cover with a cartouche (parchment paper cut to fit inside saucepan) directly over pork, to retain moisture; cover with saucepan lid. Simmer gently 1 1/2 hours, until meat is very tender and falls apart easily.
Remove pork from sauce and use 2 forks to roughly shred. Set aside.
Increase heat to high and bring liquid to a rapid simmer. Simmer uncovered for 8-10 minutes, until reduced by two thirds.
Fill dinner rolls with cheese, tomato slices, shredded pork, reduced sauce and pickles. Serve immediately.

title: chai cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a 10 inch diameter springform pan. Melt the butter in a saucepan. Remove from the heat and stir in the crushed cookies. Spread over the bottom of the pan and press down. Chill.
In a bowl, beat the sugar, cornstarch and 1/3 of the cream cheese. Beat in the chai powder and remaining cream cheese. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Spread over the cookie base.

Set the springform pan in a roasting pan and pour in hot water so that it comes about 1 inch up the side of the springform pan. Bake for 50 mins-1 hour, until the top is set but still jiggles. Allow to cool for 1 hour, then remove from the pan and allow to cool completely.
In a bowl, mix together the sour cream, lemon juice and powdered sugar until thick and creamy. Spread over the cheesecake and chill until ready to serve.

title: cauliflower crust pizza
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. In a bowl, mix the cauliflower, egg and half of the mozzarella. Season with salt. Divide into 4 portions and form into 4 flat ovals on the baking tray. Bake for 20 mins.

Meanwhile, heat the oil in a frying pan and cook the meat until crumbly. Reserve a few scallion slices for garnish, add the remainder to the pan and fry for 2 mins. Add the oregano and season with salt and black pepper. Stir in the tomatoes.

Remove the cauliflower bases from the oven and top with the meat mixture. Sprinkle with the remaining cheese. Return to the oven and bake for 12 mins, until the cheese is golden and bubbling. Sprinkle with the reserved scallions.

title: chicken, cilantro and coconut meatballs with sweet chili sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper.

Combine the ground chicken, water chestnuts, ginger, 1/3 of the cilantro, garlic and fish sauce in a bowl. Using damp hands, shape mixture into 20 balls. Roll in coconut to coat. Transfer to prepared tray. Bake 15 mins, or until golden and cooked.
Combine 1/3 of the cilantro with sweet chili sauce in a bowl. Divide rice and bok choy among serving plates. Top with meatballs. Sprinkle with remaining cilantro. Serve with chili sauce.

title: spiced lamb, couscous, and spinach salad
directions: Reserve 1 tbsp oil and place remainder in a screw-top jar with sugar, paprika, cumin, chili, garlic, and salt and pepper to taste. Shake well.
Place 2 tbsp dressing in a bowl with lamb; cover and refrigerate for 3 hours. Add lemon juice to remaining dressing.
Boil or steam carrots until tender. Drain. Place hot carrots in large serving bowl with half the dressing; toss to coat.
Heat reserved oil in a large skillet and cook lamb for 10 mins, or until browned all over and cooked to medium. Transfer to a plate; cover to keep warm.
Meanwhile, place couscous in a large heatproof bowl; add boiling water and salt to taste. Stand, covered, for 5 mins, or until water is absorbed. Fluff couscous with a fork.
Combine sliced lamb with remaining dressing, couscous, chickpeas, spinach and herbs in same bowl as carrots. Toss gently.

title: lamb and feta pizza
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Spray 2 large baking pans with no stick cooking spray. Spray a medium skillet with cooking spray. Place on medium heat. Add ground lamb and spice mix; cook, stirring with a wooden spoon to break up lumps, for 5 mins or until cooked through.
Place naan on prepared pans. Spray with cooking spray. Spread naan with lamb mixture. Top with pepper and feta.
Bake 10 mins. Combine yogurt and chopped mint in a small bowl. Top pizzas with yogurt mixture and mint leaves. Serve with salad.

title: macaroni with kabanos sausage and tomato
directions: In a large saucepan, melt butter on medium. Stir in flour and cook for 1 minute. Remove pan from heat and blend in milk until smooth. Return to heat and bring to a boil, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens. Simmer for 3 minutes. Stir in cheese and season to taste.
Cook pasta according to package instructions. Drain well and return to pan. Stir in cheese sauce.
In a frying pan, heat oil on high. Saute cabanossi for 1-2 minutes. Add tomatoes. Cook, stirring, for 1 minute. Toss with macaroni, top with chives and serve with crusty bread.

title: strawberry salad with balsamic and feta cheese
directions: In a blender, puree 1/2 the strawberries with the vinegar and sugar. Mix the remaining strawberries with the cheese and stir into the puree then set aside to marinate for about 15 mins. Season the mixture with black pepper and serve garnished with basil leaves.

title: t-bone steak with stuffed chilies and baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Wrap potatoes in foil and bake for approximately 1 hour 30 mins.
Fill chilies with cheese, wrap with Parma ham then place on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Add to oven with potatoes for final 20 mins.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a frying pan, season steaks then sear for 4-5 mins each side, depending on thickness of steaks, or until cooked to your liking. Remove from pan and let rest for 5-10 mins.
Cut open potatoes and carefully mash potato flesh and top with a little butter. Serve with steaks and stuffed chilies.

title: florentine clusters
directions: Line 2 - 12-cup muffin pans with paper liners. Combine corn flakes, coconut, pistachios and fruit in a large bowl.

Combine butter, sugar and honey in a small saucepan over low heat. Cook, stirring, for 3-4 mins, or until butter is melted and sugar dissolves. Add to corn flake mixture and mix well to combine. Distribute between paper liners and chill for 30 mins, or until firm. Drizzle melted chocolate over top of clusters to serve.

title: chicken and mushroom rigatoni
directions: Heat a grill pan on medium-high heat. Brush the chicken with 1 tsp of the oil. Cook for 4 mins each side, until just cooked through. Let stand for 5 mins, then slice thinly.

Meanwhile, heat the remaining 2 tsp oil in a large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Add leeks, mushrooms and garlic, and cook, stirring constantly, for 2 mins, until just softened. Add 2 tbsp of the stock. Reduce the heat to medium; cover and cook for 5 mins, until the leek has softened.

Increase the heat to high. Add the wine and bring to a boil. Boil for 2 mins, until reduced by half. Add the remaining stock and boil, uncovered, for 3 mins, until reduced slightly. Stir in the mustard.

Meanwhile, cook the pasta in a large saucepan of boiling water according to package directions. Drain and return to the pan. Add the chicken, leek mixture and dill. Season to taste and toss to combine. Serve immediately.

title: heart shaped chocolate and strawberry ice cream sandwiches
directions: In a bowl, using an electric mixer, beat butter and sugar together until pale and creamy. Add eggs, in two batches, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Sift flours and cocoa together. Fold into creamed mixture.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface. Knead lightly, press together and divide in half. Shape each piece into a disc shape. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill 30 minutes.
Line a baking tray with parchment paper, allowing 1/2 inch overhang. Spread ice-cream evenly over tray. Smooth surface and cover with parchment paper. Freeze until very firm (about 2 hours).
Preheat oven to 350°F. Line two baking trays with parchment paper.
Roll out each dough disc between two sheets of parchment paper until 3mm thick. Using a 2 1/2 inch heart-shaped cutter, cut eight cookies from each dough sheet. Transfer to trays. Chill 15 minutes.
Bake 15-20 minutes, until cooked, cool on tray for 5 minutes. Transfer to wire rack to cool completely.

Lift ice-cream onto a board. Peel off top layer of paper. Using heart-shaped cutter, cut out eight hearts. Sandwich each ice-cream heart between two cookies. Return to the freezer until ready to serve.
To decorate, make a small heart template from parchment paper. Place on top of the cookies and dust with powdered sugar. Remove template and top cookies with half a strawberry.

title: rosemary and garlic lamb with mango chutney
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. To make the mango chutney, heat 1 tbsp oil in a saucepan and saute onion, ginger and 1 clove garlic for 2 mins. Add mango, pepper and saute over medium heat for 5 mins. Add coconut milk and simmer for 5 mins. Add lime juice, curry powder, cayenne and salt to taste. Remove from heat and allow to cool.

Meanwhile, heat 1 tbsp oil in a saucepan and saute rosemary and remaining garlic for 1 min. Remove from heat. Heat remaining oil, season lamb then sear until browned on all sides. Spread rosemary and garlic mixture over lamb and place on prepared baking tray. Roast for 8-10 mins. Remove from oven and allow to rest for 5 mins. Garnish with rosemary and serve with mango chutney.

title: mackerel with halloumi and corn salad
directions: Preheat grill or grill pan over high heat.
Combine 5 tbsp oil, basil, lemon zest and lemon juice. Rub 2/3 over fish. Season. Set aside.

Toss corn and zucchini with remaining oil. Season. Grill corn for 3-4 mins, until tender and lightly charred. Grill zucchini strips for 1 min per side, until grill marks appear. Set aside. Slice kernels off corn cob and add to zucchini. Grill halloumi for 1-2 mins, until golden. Add to zucchini and corn mixture.
Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Saute fish for 3-4 mins per side, until golden and flesh flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve fish with salad and lemon wedges. Drizzle remaining basil mixture over top.

title: ginger star cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line baking sheets with parchment paper. Beat butter and brown sugar in a medium bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed until light and creamy. Add egg yolk and syrup; beat until combined. Sift flour, baking soda, ginger and cinnamon over butter mixture; stir to combine. Press dough into a ball.

Roll dough between sheets of baking paper to 1/8 inch thickness. Using a 2 inch star cookie cutter, cut stars from dough. Re-roll remaining dough, if necessary. Place stars on prepared pans. Bake for 10 mins or until golden brown. Cool in pan 2 minutes. Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.

For the lemon icing, using a wooden spoon, beat egg white in a medium bowl. Gradually add sifted powdered sugar, a few tablespoons at a time. Continue to beat until smooth. Add lemon juice; beat until combined. Spoon icing into a small resealable plastic bag. Snip a small corner from bag. Pipe icing onto cookies. Decorate with dragees. Let stand until icing is set.

title: cinnamon chicken with carrot salad
directions: Score chicken in 2-3 places using a sharp knife. Rub with cinnamon.
For the carrot salad, combine all ingredients in a bowl and season to taste. Cover and chill until needed.
Heat oil in a large frying pan on high. Cook chicken, skin-side down, 4-5 mins each side, until golden and cooked through. Stir in lemon zest. Top with extra zest and serve with salad.

title: omelette and prosciutto roll
directions: For the fillings, combine ricotta, Parmesan and garlic in a bowl. Season to taste. Heat arugula in a small frying pan on high heat 2 mins, until wilted. Squeeze out liquid and chop roughly.

For the omelette, heat oil in an 8 x 12 inch flameproof nonstick baking dish on medium heat. Add eggs and cook 6-8 mins, until just set. Transfer to a flat surface. Spread with prosciutto. Top with ricotta mixture and arugula. Roll to enclose fillings, slice and serve.

title: cantonese beef patties with gai lan
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, ginger, chili pepper, water chestnuts, chives, egg, breadcrumbs, 1 tbsp hoisin sauce and two-thirds of the garlic in large bowl; shape mixture into eight patties.
Combine 1 tbsp water, oyster sauce, 1/3 cup hoisin sauce and remaining garlic in small bowl. Reserve 1/4 cup hoisin mixture for serving.
Brush patties with remaining hoisin mixture. Cook patties on heated oiled grill pan or large skillet until browned both sides and cooked through.
Heat sesame oil on grill pan or skillet. Cook gai lan until wilted. Serve gai lan topped with patties; drizzle with reserved hoisin mixture.

title: pad thai
directions: Prepare the noodles according to the package directions, then drain well and set aside.
Heat the oil in a wok over a high heat. Stir-fry the onion and garlic for 1 min. Mix in the chicken and shrimp and stir-fry for 4-5 mins, until cooked.
