To make the sauce, caramelize the sugar in a frying pan over a low heat. In a separate pan, heat the wine and vinegar. Pour the caramelized sugar into the wine and vinegar, add the shallots, then simmer, without covering, for about 15 minutes.

Heat 3 tbsp oil in a pan, remove the meat from the marinade and fry on each side for about 3 minutes. Pour the marinade through a sieve and add the collected garlic and herbs to the lamb for the final minute of cooking. Slice the meat diagonally and serve with the garlic, herbs, caramelized shallots, sauce and roasted potatoes.

title: duck confit with duck fat fried potatoes and pear and watercress salad
directions: Using a sharp knife, cut legs and breasts off ducks. Remove as much fat as possible from carcasses and reserve. Discard wings and carcasses.
Combine duck pieces, salt, garlic, bay leaf, thyme and peppercorns in a medium bowl. Cover and refrigerate until required.
Meanwhile, place reserved fat in a large saucepan. Cook over low heat for 1 hour, or until fat has melted. Strain mixture through a fine-mesh sieve into a large bowl. Discard solids.
Preheat oven to 300°F.

Rinse duck pieces under cold running water then pat dry with paper towels. Arrange duck, in single layer, in a large baking dish. Reserve 2 tbsp duck fat then pour remaining fat over duck. Top up with olive oil, making sure duck is completely submerged. Transfer to oven to confit for 2 hours.
To make the duck fat fried potatoes, boil, steam or microwave potatoes until tender. Drain. Heat reserved fat in a large frying pan. Cook potatoes, in batches, until browned. Cover to keep warm.
To make the pear and watercress salad, whisk together mustard, vinegar, sugar and oil. Place watercress, pear and dressing in a large bowl and toss gently to combine.
Cook duck in a large frying pan, skin-side down, until skin is crispy. Serve with potatoes and salad.

title: warm potato salad with mushrooms and bacon
directions: Heat a frying pan and add the bacon. Cook for 4-5 mins then add the spring onions and mushrooms. Saute for 3-4 mins. Stir in the mustard and stock and simmer for 1-2 mins. Add the vinegar and season. Toss with the potatoes and serve.

title: tuna niçoise
directions: Melt butter and 1 tbsp of the oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Add potato and thyme; cook for 6 mins or until tender.

Preheat a grill pan on medium heat. Brush tuna with half the remaining oil. Cook for 1-2 mins each side for rare. Transfer to a plate. Let stand, loosely covered with foil, 5 mins, then cut into 3/4-inch cubes.
Place eggs in a medium saucepan and cover with water. Bring to a boil. Remove pan from heat. Let stand 8 mins; drain. Cool eggs under cold water. Peel and halve eggs.
Cook beans in boiling water for 1 min or until tender. Refresh under cold water.
Combine tuna, vegetables, remaining oil and herbs in a large bowl. Serve with egg and lemon wedges.

title: pesto-marinated chicken drumsticks
directions: For the pesto, pulse the pine nuts with the basil, garlic and cheese. Gradually drizzle in the oil and lemon juice. Toss with the drumsticks. Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Preheat the oven to 425°F. Place the drumsticks in a baking dish and bake for about 30 mins. Turn on the broiler and broil the drumsticks for another 5 mins. Let cool slightly before serving.

title: apricot upside-down cakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a 12-hole muffin pan. Line the bases with parchment paper.
Sprinkle the tablespoon of brown sugar equally into the holes. Add 1 apricot half cut-side down, to each hole.
Using an electric mixer, beat eggs and brown sugar in a medium bowl until light and fluffy. Stir in the almonds, vanilla, flour and milk then the divide mixture among the holes.
Bake for 20 mins. Allow to stand for 5 mins then turn onto a wire rack. Brush the apricot jam over the hot cakes. Serve the cakes warm or at room temperature.

title: beef bourguignon pies
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Lightly grease four 1 1/3-cup ramekins. Place on a baking sheet.

Melt butter in a large skillet on medium heat. Saute onion and mushrooms for 3-4 mins, until tender. Add flour. Cook, stirring to coat vegetables, for 2 mins, until lightly browned. Remove from heat. Stir in stock until smooth. Add thyme and bay leaf. Return to heat and cook, stirring, until sauce boils and thickens. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 3 mins. Stir in wine. Add meat and return to a boil on high heat. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 3-4 mins.
Divide mixture among ramekins. Cut pastry sheet into 4 squares. Brush rims of ramekins with egg yolk. Cover with pastry and trim edges. Make a slit in top of each pie and brush tops with egg yolk.
Bake for 15 mins, until pastry is crisp and golden. Serve with sauteed spinach.

title: sweet corn soup with fried tortillas
directions: Place the onion and half the oil in a medium saucepan and add 1 tbsp water. Cover and cook gently for 10 mins, or until onion is tender and translucent. Add garlic and ginger and cook for 1 min.
Add corn kernels, potatoes, salt and stock or water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; partially cover with a lid and simmer for 45 mins, stirring occasionally.
Mash half the soup with a potato masher or puree with immersion blender. Add to remaining soup in saucepan. Taste and adjust seasoning, adding more salt if necessary. Swirl in the cream.
Heat remaining oil in a small skillet on medium-low heat. Cook tortilla strips until light brown. Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with sea salt, smoked paprika and lime peel. Serve with soup.

title: jasmine rice
directions: Wash rice thoroughly until the water runs clear. Bring 2 cups water to the boil in a medium saucepan with a tight-fitting lid. Add rice and a pinch of salt and boil, partially covered, for 5 mins, or until holes start to appear in the surface of the rice.

Cover completely with the lid (do not remove the lid again until rice is completely cooked) and turn the heat down as low as possible. Cook for 10 mins. Remove the pan from the heat and let stand for 10 mins. Remove the lid and fluff with fork.

title: bacon and mushroom risotto
directions: Melt butter in a large pan. Cook onion for 2 mins. Add mushrooms and cook for 3-4 mins. Add risotto rice and stir to coat. Add 4 cups water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 12 mins, until most water has been absorbed.
Meanwhile, cook bacon until crispy. Chop. Add to risotto. Serve garnished with parsley and cherry tomatoes.

title: steak pizzaiola
directions: Heat 2 tbsp of the oil in a large skillet on high heat. Season steaks. Cook for 1 min each side or until well seared. Transfer to a plate and cover with foil to keep warm.

Heat remaining 2 tbsp oil in same pan on medium heat. Saute garlic for 30 seconds. Add tomatoes and bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 8-10 mins, or until sauce thickens. Stir in olives, basil and sugar. Season to taste.
Return steaks to pan with sauce and simmer, covered, for 1-2 mins or until heated through.
Serve steaks topped with sauce and sprinkled with feta and additional basil leaves. Accompany with crusty bread and green salad.

title: honeybee heart cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Lightly grease and line an 8 inch heart- shape (or 9 inch round) cake pan with parchment paper.
In a bowl, combine the flour and sugar. In a separate bowl, whisk the butter, sour cream, eggs and honey together. Fold into the flour mixture.

Spoon into the prepared cake pan and smooth surface. Bake for 50-60 mins, until firm to the touch and a skewer inserted into the cake comes out clean. Cool in the pan for 5 mins. Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
For the buttercream, place the butter in a bowl and using an electric mixer, beat until very pale. Gradually add half the powdered sugar until combined. Beat in milk and remaining powdered sugar.
Level the top of the cake using a serrated knife. Spread with buttercream and arrange bees around cake to serve.

title: lamb with parmesan and sun-dried tomato dumplings
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Heat oil in a Dutch oven on medium-high heat. Cook lamb, in batches, for 2-3 mins or until seared. Transfer to a heatproof plate.

Add onion, celery and carrot to pan. Cook and stir for 5 mins or until onion softens. Return lamb to pan. Add garlic, pasta sauce, crumbled stock cube, 1 1/3 cups water, Worcestershire sauce and bay leaves. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Cover with tight-fitting lid. Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Meanwhile, place flour in a medium bowl. Rub in butter to make fine crumbs. Add milk, tomato and oregano. With a spatula, use a cutting motion to mix until a dough forms. Shape into 12 balls.

Increase oven temperature to 425°F. Add fava beans to lamb mixture. Arrange dumplings over lamb. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake, uncovered, for 10-15 mins or until dumplings are golden brown and cooked through.

title: chili tomato chicken
directions: Toss chicken in flour, shaking away excess. Heat oil in large saucepan on medium-high heat. Cook chicken, in batches, until browned. Remove from pan.
Add onion, garlic, nuts, chili pepper and bacon to pan. Cook, stirring, until onion is soft. Stir in tomato, stock, basil, tomato paste, wine and olives; bring to a boil.
Add chicken. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, about 45 mins or until chicken is tender.

title: tropical fruit trifle
directions: Whip cream to soft peaks. Gently fold in meringue. Add 1/2 the chopped fruit and 1 tbsp passion fruit pulp. Distribute 1/2 between 6 serving glasses. Top with 1/2 the remaining fruit then remaining cream mixture and remaining fruit. Serve.

title: chicken and broccolini tagliatelle
directions: Cook tagliatelle in a large pan of boiling salted water according to package directions. Drain and return to pan.
Meanwhile, cook chicken in a heated, oiled large skillet until golden and just cooked through. Remove chicken from pan. Cool slightly and slice.

Add garlic to skillet; cook and stir until fragrant. Add cream and bouillon cube, stirring until mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Add broccolini and simmer for 3 mins or until broccolini is tender. Stir in chicken.
Add chicken and broccolini sauce to hot pasta; toss to combine. Season with freshly ground black pepper.

title: pork roll with cranberry chestnut stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Heat oil in a frying pan and cook garlic and spinach for 2-3 mins. Set aside to cool. Flatten pork steaks with a rolling pin until 1/2 inch thick.

Place an 18 x 20 inch piece of foil on the work surface. Arrange bacon on foil, leaving a 4 inch border. Arrange pork on top, then cover with spinach, chestnuts and cranberry jelly. Season to taste. Roll up, wrapping in foil and twisting foil ends to seal. Place on a baking sheet.
Bake for 1 hr. Remove foil; drain off juices. Drizzle with honey and return to oven for 10 mins. Let rest for 10 minutes, then slice and serve.

title: aussie ground beef toasts
directions: Heat oil in a large frying pan on medium. Cook onion 3 mins, stirring, until soft. Add beef and cook 5 mins, breaking up lumps, until browned. Stir in flour. Add stock, tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce. Bring to a boil then reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 30 mins. Stir in parsley. Top with parsley sprigs and serve on toast.

title: creamy butternut squash, mushroom and ricotta penne
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Line a large baking pan with parchment paper. Arrange squash and mushrooms on prepared pan and drizzle with oil. Sprinkle with thyme and season to taste. Wrap garlic in foil and place on pan.
Bake 30-35 mins, until squash is tender.
Cook pasta in large saucepan of boiling salted water according to package directions.
Squeeze garlic from skins and mash with a fork. Place garlic, 1/2 of the squash, tomatoes and cream in a blender. Add any roasting juices from mushrooms. Blend until smooth. Season to taste.
Drain pasta and return to pan with squash puree; toss to coat. Add remaining pumpkin and mushrooms. Serve topped with ricotta and additional thyme.

title: horseradish mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender, around 12-15 mins. Drain. Return to pot and mash with remaining ingredients. Season.

title: raspberry tiramisu cake
directions: Whisk together 1/3 cup hot water, espresso powder and liqueur. Set aside.

In a food processor, combine cottage cheese, sugar and vanilla extract. Process for 2 mins, or until smooth. Add cream cheese and process for 2 mins. Add mascarpone and pulse until smooth. Transfer to a large bowl and fold in whipped cream.

Lightly grease an 8 inch springform pan. Line base with sliced chocolate cupcake. Brush with 1/3 of the coffee mixture. Spread 1 3/4 cups mascarpone mixture over top. Repeat layers 2 more times. Chill overnight.
Transfer tiramisu to a serving platter and sift cocoa powder over top. Garnish with raspberries, white chocolate curls and chocolate espresso beans.

title: french fry seasoning mix
directions: MIx together all ingredients. Sprinkle over hot French fries and season.

title: turkish lamb and spinach flatbread
directions: Sift flour and salt into a large bowl. Gradually stir in 1 1/2 cups warm water, mixing to form a firm dough.
Knead dough on floured surface about 5 mins, or until smooth and elastic. Return to bowl. Cover with a clean tea towel.

For the filling, heat oil in a large skillet on high heat. Saute onion and garlic 3-4 mins, until tender. Stir in cumin, sumac and red pepper flakes; cook 1 min. Add ground lamb; cook 4-5 mins, until browned. Transfer mixture to a bowl. Cool 10 mins. Stir in cheese and spinach; season to taste.
Divide dough into 6 portions. Roll each piece into a 16 x 12-inch rectangle. Spoon filling evenly over one half of each rectangle. Fold over dough to enclose filling. Fold edges under to seal.
Wipe skillet clean. Heat on medium heat. Brush flatbread with oil; cook 3-4 mins each side, until browned and crisp. Repeat with remaining flatbread. Cut into squares. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: cod fillet with potato and bacon salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water for 20 mins. Drain then rinse under cold water to cool slightly. Slice.
Heat a frying pan. Saute bacon and onions briefly. Add stock and vinegar. Bring to a boil. Season and add mustard. Pour over potatoes. Fold in herbs and set aside for 1 hour to marinate.

Meanwhile, drizzle fish with lemon juice. Beat together egg yolk, beer and flour until smooth. Whisk egg white until stiff and fold into batter. Heat oil in a deep fat fryer to 350°F. Season fish, dip into batter and deep fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Serve fish with potato salad. Garnish with reserved herbs and lemon wedges.

title: caraway lamb triangles
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line 2 baking pans with parchment paper.

Spray the onion with no stick cooking spray. Heat a large skillet on medium heat. Cook and stir the onion for 2 mins. Add the ground lamb and cook, stirring with a wooden spoon to break up the lumps, for 3-4 mins or until browned. Stir in the garlic and spice and cook for 30 seconds or until fragrant. Remove from the heat. Stir in the carrot, almonds and cilantro and mix well.

For each triangle, place 1 sheet of phyllo on work surface. Spray with cooking spray. Fold in half lengthwise, twice, to make a long, thin strip. Spoon 1 heaping tablespoon of filling onto one end of the strip. Fold phyllo over to cover filling, forming a triangle. Continue folding, keeping triangle shape, until the end of the phyllo strip. Place on the prepared pans. Spray the triangles with cooking spray and sprinkle with caraway seeds.
Bake for 12-15 mins or until golden. Serve with pesto for dipping.

title: easy tomato and pesto pizzas
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Mix together the tomato paste, oil and 4 tablespoons water. Season to taste.

Place the breads on baking sheets and spread with the tomato mixture. Top with the tomato slices and artichokes. Dot with the pesto and cheese slices. Bake for 10 minutes until the cheese is melting. Serve scattered with basil leaves.

title: smoked trout, caper and dill frittata
directions: Heat oil in a deep 8-inch skillet on high heat. Saute onion for 1-2 mins until tender. Stir in trout and remove pan from heat. Reduce heat to low.

Mix eggs, ricotta, capers and dill in a large bowl. Pour over onion and trout in pan. Return pan to heat and cook for 4-5 mins until frittata begins to brown on the bottom and become firm. Meanwhile, preheat broiler to high.
Place pan under hot broiler for 3-4 mins until frittata is golden and set. Serve in wedges garnished with additional dill.

title: flower bouquet
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Line 18 muffin cups with paper liners.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Divide among muffin cups. Bake and cool according to package directions.
Tint half of the frosting with yellow food color. Tint remaining frosting with pink food color. Spread on cooled cupcakes.

Using scissors, cut marshmallows in half. Squeeze ends of each marshmallow together to form petals. Decorate each cupcake with 7 marshmallow petals. Place a Skittle into the center of each cupcake. Position cupcakes on a platter or cake board.

On surface dusted with sifted powdered sugar, knead fondant until smooth. Knead green food color into fondant. Divide fondant into quarters. Roll one-quarter of the fondant into a thin rope. Keep remaining fondant wrapped in plastic wrap. Cut rope into uneven lengths; position on board for the stems. Repeat with remaining fondant to make 18 stems in total.
Pinch stems together near ends; secure bow with a little frosting. Position spearmint leaves along stems; secure with a little frosting.

title: chinese beef and broccoli
directions: Combine beef, garlic and 2 tbsp soy sauce. Cover and chill for 30 mins to marinate.
Oil a large wok or frying pan and place over high heat. Working in batches, stir-fry beef until browned. Remove from wok and set aside.
Add broccoli to wok and stir-fry for 1-2 mins.
Blend cornstarch with sherry, remaining soy sauce and 2/3 cup water. Add to wok along with beef. Cook, tossing, until liquid boils and thickens. Serve.

title: chicken parmigiana-style
directions: Split chicken breasts in half horizontally. Toss chicken in flour, shaking away excess. Dip chicken pieces, one at a time, in combined egg and milk, then in breadcrumbs.
Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat. Shallow-fry chicken, in batches, until browned and cooked through. Drain on paper towels.
Meanwhile, preheat the broiler.
Place chicken on baking pan. Spread with pasta sauce. Top with ham then sprinkle with cheese. Broil 2-3 mins until cheese melts.

title: mini blueberry and apricot loaves
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease 8 mini loaf pans.
To make the topping, combine cereal, nuts and coconut. Mix in butter and honey until well combined. Set aside.

Cream butter and sugar until pale. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Fold in flour and baking soda alternately with milk. Fold in blueberries and apricots. Mix until just combined. Distribute between prepared pans. Sprinkle with topping, pressing down slightly. Bake for 35-40 mins, until golden and a skewer inserted in the center comes out clean. Let cool in pan for 10 mins.
Serve warm, dusted with powdered sugar.

title: marble brownie cake with snow caps
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Grease and line a 12 x 15 inch baking pan. For the chocolate cake mix, melt the dark chocolate and 2/3 cup of the butter in a saucepan over a low heat.
Separate 2 eggs. With an electric hand whisk, beat 2 eggs, 1 egg yolk, a pinch of the salt and 3/4 cup of the sugar for 4-5 mins. Stir into the melted chocolate.
Place 1 cup of of the flour in a bowl with 1 tsp of the baking powder. Stir the dark chocolate and egg mixture into the flour.
For the white cake mix, melt the white chocolate with the remaining butter in a saucepan over a low heat.
With an electric hand whisk, beat 2 eggs, 1 egg yolk, a pinch of the salt and 3/4 cup of the sugar for 4-5 mins. Stir into the white chocolate.

Place 1 1/4 cups of the flour in a bowl with the remaining baking powder and the nuts and add the white chocolate and egg mixture. In alternating spoonfuls fill the baking pan with both batters. Bake for 25 mins. Remove from the oven and allow to cool for 10 mins in the pan.
Meanwhile, beat the egg whites and remaining salt until stiff. Gradually beat in the remaining sugar. Continue beating until the egg whites are glossy.

Place the egg white mix into a disposable piping bag fitted with a medium round nozzle. Pipe small tufts on top of the cake, and return to the oven for a further 10-15 mins. Allow to cool completely in the pan a wire rack. Cut into squares.

title: glazed pork neck with mustard potatoes and green beans
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°F. Using a mortar and pestle, grind the allspice, chili flakes, 1 tsp salt and 2 star anise to a fine powder. Rub all over the pork and place in a roasting pan. Place onions around the pork and roast for 1 hour 15 mins.

In a bowl, mix the grated lemon zest, chopped garlic, wholegrain mustard, 5 tbsp oil and 1 1/2 tsp salt. Add the potatoes and mix well. In a separate bowl, mix the honey, Dijon mustard and soy sauce. Add the potatoes to the pork and roast for 1 hour, gradually pouring in 1 cup water at intervals. After 20 mins, brush the honey glaze over the pork and add remaining star anise. Test temperature for doneness.

Cook the beans in boiling salted water for 10 mins. Drain. Heat the butter and 2 tbsp oil in a frying pan and saute the almonds and garlic slices for 1 min. Add the lemon juice and zest strips and bring to a boil. Add a pinch of sugar and season to taste. Add the beans and oregano.
Arrange the pork on a board or serving plate, drizzle with pan juices and garnish with oregano. Serve with the potatoes and beans.

title: sesame pork meatballs with singapore noodles
directions: Combine ground pork, 2 tbsp oyster sauce, soy sauce, kecap manis, sesame oil, cilantro root and garlic. Season. Roll tablespoonfuls of mixture into balls. Toss in flour, shaking off excess, then coat in sesame seeds. Arrange on a baking tray and chill for 10 mins.
Heat oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook meatballs for 8-10 mins, turning, until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.
Drain oil from pan, leaving 1 tbsp oil in pan. Stir-fry bok choy for 1-2 mins, until just wilted. Add remaining oyster sauce and toss to combine.
Prepare noodles according to package instructions. Serve meatballs with noodles and bok choy. Sprinkle with reserved cilantro leaves.

title: miso udon soup with shrimp and tofu
directions: Cook noodles according to packet instructions. Set aside.
In a medium saucepan, combine 6 cups water, miso and mustard. Whisk over medium heat to dissolve. Bring to a boil then add shrimp. Cook for 1-2 min, or until just pink. Remove shrimp from broth.
Distribute noodles, shrimp and tofu between 4 serving bowls. Top with vegetables. Pour hot soup over top then sprinkle with spring onions and nori to serve.

title: sausage and cheddar frittata
directions: Preheat broiler. Whisk together eggs, milk and parsley. Heat oil in an 8 inch nonstick frying pan. Cook sausages and mushrooms for 6-8 mins, or until sausages are cooked through. Let cool slightly then cut sausages in half lengthwise.

Arrange tomatoes, sausages and mushrooms in frying pan. Place over low heat. Pour egg mixture over meat and vegetables and stir briefly to distribute mixture. Cook, without stirring, for 3 mins, or until slightly firm around the edges. Sprinkle with cheese.
Transfer to oven and broil for 3 mins, or until top is golden and set. Serve sprinkled with extra parsley.

title: baked potatoes with beans and smoked cheddar
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Place the potatoes on a baking pan and drizzle with olive oil. Bake for 1 hour or until tender. Season. Cool on the tray for 5 mins.

Cut a cross in the potatoes and squeeze upwards from the bottom. Top with the baked beans and cheese. Season to taste. Bake for a further 5 mins until the cheese has melted. Garnish with parsley and serve.

title: tofu and chinese long bean fried rice
directions: Heat a wok or large frying pan over medium-high heat. Add 1 tsp oil and swirl to coat surface. Add beans and stir-fry for 8 mins, or until lightly charred and tender. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

Combine cornstarch and five-spice powder. Toss tofu in mixture, shaking off excess. Heat extra oil in a large heavy-bottomed saucepan over medium heat. Working in batches, deep-fry tofu for 1-2 mins, or until golden brown and crisp. Drain on paper towels then cut in half.

Add remaining oil to wok over medium heat. Stir-fry garlic, ginger, onions and chili for 30 seconds, or until fragrant. Return beans to wok. Add rice and soy sauce. Stir-fry for 2-3 mins, or until lightly browned. Add tofu and toss to combine. Serve.

title: fruit and nut trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl. Store in an airtight container.

title: brandied date cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°F. Line base and side of deep 8 inch-round cake pan with 3 layers of parchment paper, bringing paper 2 inches above edge of pan.

Beat butter, cheese and sugar until combined. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing until combined between additions. Mix in flour and 1/4 cup brandy and mix until smooth. Fold in dates and citrus peel. Transfer to prepared pan and bake for 1 hour 30 mins.
Brush hot cake with extra brandy. Cover pan tightly with foil and let cake cool in pan.
Dust with powdered sugar to serve.

title: mushroom crepes with cilantro sauce
directions: For the crepes, whisk eggs, salt, flour, milk and oil in a medium bowl until smooth. Cover; let stand for 30 mins.

Meanwhile, for the mushroom filling, heat butter and oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Cook onion, garlic and chili pepper, stirring, until onion softens. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring, for 15 mins or until mushrooms are soft and water has evaporated. Cool slightly; stir in cilantro. Season to taste.

Heat an oiled heavy-bottomed crepe pan or small skillet on low heat. Pour about 3 tbsp of batter into pan, tilting pan to coat the bottom. Cook crepe until lightly browned, loosening the edge of the crepe with a spatula. Turn crepe; brown the other side. Remove crepe from pan; cover to keep warm. Repeat with remaining batter to make a total of 12 crepes.
Preheat the oven to 350°F.
Place heaped tablespoons of filling along center of each crepe; roll crepes to enclose filling. Place crepes, in a single layer, in an oiled shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake for 15 mins or until filling is heated through and cheese is lightly browned.

Meanwhile, for the cilantro sauce, heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Cook onion and garlic, stirring, until onion softens. Add cream; simmer, uncovered, for 10 mins or until thickened. Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream, cilantro and cheese. Season to taste.
Serve crepes with sauce.

title: spicy chicken and squash meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Line base and sides of an 8 inch springform pan with parchment paper. Combine cilantro, ground chicken, fish sauce, chili, onions, eggs, breadcrumbs and 1/3 cup chili sauce. Transfer to prepared pan. Top with squash, pressing into surface. Bake for 45 mins.
Drizzle with remaining chili sauce and bake for 15 mins, or until glazed and cooked through. Let cool for 10 mins then cut into wedges and serve.

title: cinnamon and pear oatmeal
directions: Bring oats and milk to a boil, stirring constantly. Add chopped pears and simmer for 8-10 mins, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and stir in honey and cinnamon.
Spoon into 2 serving bowls. Top with strawberries and serve with extra milk and honey.

title: pork kebabs with tzatziki and greek salad
directions: To make tzatziki, peel half the cucumber and coarsely grate into a bowl, then stir in the garlic and yogurt. Season to taste, cover and chill. Cut the rest of the cucumber into chunks and mix with the feta, tomatoes, olives, yellow pepper and parsley. Thinly slice one of the onions and scatter over the salad. Drizzle the salad with vinegar and half the olive oil and season to taste.

Cut the remaining onions into wedges and thread onto 8 metal skewers, alternating with orange pepper chunks and cubed pork. Sprinkle with paprika and season well. Heat the rest of the oil in a large frying pan and fry the skewers over high heat until browned on all sides. Cook over medium heat for a further 15-20 mins, turning frequently until the pork is cooked through.
Divide the salad between 4 plates and serve with the pork skewers and tzatziki.

title: shrimp and tomato pasta salad
directions: Whisk together olive oil, lemon juice and Dijon mustard. Season. Set aside.
In a serving bowl, combine shrimp, pasta, tomatoes, avocado, arugula and green onions. Toss with 1/2 the dressing. Serve with remaining dressing on the side.

title: singapore noodles
directions: Place noodles in a large bowl. Cover with boiling water. Separate strands with a fork. Drain.

Heat 2 tsp peanut oil in a wok or large frying pan over high heat. Add eggs and swirl to coat base. Cook for 1-2 mins, until set. Flip over and cook for 30 seconds. Remove from pan, roll up and slice thinly. Set aside.
Add remaining peanut oil to wok. Stir-fry chicken for 2-3 mins, until browned. Transfer to a plate.

Add snow peas, carrot, garlic and chili to wok. Stir-fry for 1-2 mins, until tender. Return chicken to wok along with soy sauce and oyster sauce. Add noodles and stir-fry for 2-3 mins, until heated through. Serve topped with spring onions and omelette.

title: peach and ginger chutney
directions: Heat oil in a large, heavy-based saucepan on medium. Saute onion, garlic, ginger, chile, curry powder, and spice 3-4 minutes, until onion is tender and mixture is fragrant.
Add peaches, vinegar, and sugar. Stir until sugar dissolves. Increase heat to high and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium and simmer 25-30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture thickens.
Allow to cool completely before transferring to sterilized jars.

title: lemon panna cotta pots
directions: Pour cream into a medium saucepan; add the sugar and vanilla extract. Cook and stir on low speed until warm. Sprinkle the gelatin over the cream mixture; stir until dissolved. Do not boil.
Pour the cream mixture through a fine sieve into a large bowl. Stir in the lemon peel and juice. Cool.
Pour the mixture into eight 2/3-cup teacups or serving dishes. Place on a tray and cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight. Serve the lemon panna cotta in the teacups.

title: lemon butter green beans
directions: Blanch green beans in boiling salted water for 3 mins, or until tender. Drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter over medium heat. Cook scallion for 1 min. Add green beans, lemon pepper seasoning, oregano and lemon juice, tossing to coat. Serve warm.

title: steamed ginger fish with rice
directions: Cook rice in a large saucepan of boiling salted water for 10-12 mins, until just tender. Drain.
Meanwhile, bring a wok or large pan of water to a boil. Season fish to taste. Place 1/2 the ginger in a lined bamboo steamer basket. Top with fish and remaining ginger.
Place covered steamer basket over simmering water. Steam for 5-6 mins. Sprinkle fish with 1/2 each of the onion and cilantro. Continue steaming for a further 5-6 mins, until cooked when tested.
Heat soy and oil in a small saucepan on medium heat, stirring, for 1-2 mins.
Transfer fish to serving plates. Drizzle with soy mixture. Sprinkle with remaining onion and cilantro.
Serve fish with rice and lime wedges.

title: potato, lima bean and chicken salad
directions: Place potatoes in a medium saucepan of salted water. Bring to boil on high. Reduce heat to medium and simmer 10-12 mins, until just tender. Drain well. Transfer to a bowl. Add lima beans, mint, mayonnaise and vinegar. Toss well and season to taste. Fold in the chicken and serve.

title: fish ball and eggplant red curry
directions: Blend or process fish with garlic, cilantro roots and stems, soy sauce and cornstarch until mixture forms a smooth paste. Roll heaping teaspoons of mixture into balls.

Heat oil and curry paste in a large saucepan on medium-high heat, stirring until fragrant. Add coconut milk; bring to a boil, stirring, until combined. Add fish balls and eggplant. Reduce heat to low; simmer, uncovered, for 5 mins, or until fish balls are cooked through. Add sugar, lime juice, fish sauce and onions; stir until sugar dissolves.
Spoon into serving bowl. Sprinkle with bean sprouts, chili pepper and cilantro leaves.

title: couscous and vegetable salad
directions: Combine 1 2/3 cups boiling water with reserved oil, seasoning and lemon zest and lemon juice. Add couscous, cover and set aside for 4 mins. Fluff up with a fork and season. Fold in arugula.
Serve couscous topped with eggplant, tomatoes and a dollop of tzatziki.

title: crispy milk and date pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease 4 - 5 inch pie dishes. Place on a baking tray.
To make the date jam, bring dates, sugar and 1/2 cup water to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 5-6 mins, until thick. Let cool.

Brush 2 sheets of filo dough with butter and layer together. Spread 1/4 of the date jam along center then scrunch short ends towards each other in even folds (like a fan without pleats). Roll up into a loose spiral and fit inside of a prepared dish. Repeat with remaining filo dough, butter and jam. Bake for 8-10 mins, until pastry is crisp and slightly golden.

Meanwhile, combine cream and milk in a small saucepan. Stir over medium heat until almost boiling. Remove from heat. Whisk together egg yolks, sugar and vanilla. Gradually whisk in milk until combined. Pour over filo dough. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar. Bake for another 10-15 mins, until firm.
Serve dusted with powdered sugar.

title: ham, cheese and tomato chutney wraps
directions: Spread flatbreads with chutney. Top with spinach, cheese and ham.
Roll to enclose. Cut into halves.

title: easy raisin buns
directions: Preheat oven to very hot 425°F. Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Sift the flour into a large bowl, then add the butter. Using fingertips, lightly rub in 2 tbsp butter until it is well combined. Stir in the raisins and 2 tbsp sugar.

Make a well in the center of the flour mixture. In a separate bowl, whisk together the milk and egg. Reserve 1 tbsp of mixture and pour remainder into the well. Using a palette knife, quickly mix to create a soft, sticky dough. Do not over-mix.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly. Break the dough into 9 even-sized pieces, and roll into narrow buns about 4 inches long.
Place the buns close together on the prepared tray. Brush with the reserved milk mixture and bake for 12-15 mins, until the buns sound hollow when tapped.
Remove from the oven. In a small dish, combine 1 tbsp just-boiled water and 1 tbsp sugar and brush over the buns. Allow to cool on a wire rack.
To make the icing: combine the powdered sugar, water and 1 tsp butter in a bowl. Add the food coloring, as desired, and mix well. Spread a strip down the centre of each bun. Serve.

title: orange and cherry frangipane tart
directions: With a baking pan on center shelf, preheat oven to 400°F. Use pie crusts to line bottom and sides of a 1 inch-deep, 13 x 4 inch rectangular tart pan with a removable bottom, trimming as necessary. Trim edges; refrigerate for 30 mins.

Line crust with parchment paper; fill halfway with dried beans. Place tart pan on preheated pan; bake tor 10 mins. Remove beans and paper; bake for 5-8 mins or until pastry is golden. Cool on a wire rack. Reduce oven temperature to 350°F.

Beat butter, sugar, egg and orange peel in a medium bowl with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Stir in almonds and flour. Spread mixture into tart crust. Toss cherries in cornstarch. Press cherries into almond mixture.
Bake for 35-40 mins or until golden and firm to the touch. Cool on a wire rack.

title: olive oil bearnaise
directions: In a small saucepan, combine vinegar, tarragon sprigs and peppercorns. Simmer for 1-2 mins, until reduced by 1/2. Strain.

In a large heatproof bowl, whisk together egg yolks and strained vinegar reduction. Place over a saucepan of simmering water. Whisk vigorously for 1-2 mins, until thick and creamy. Remove from heat. Gradually add oil in a thin steady stream, whisking to combine (if sauce becomes too thick, slowly whisk in a little warm water). Mix in extra chopped tarragon. Season to taste.

title: almond chicken stir-fry
directions: Heat 1 tsp of the oil in a wok on high heat. Stir-fry the nuts until lightly browned. Remove from the wok.
Heat the remaining oil in the wok on high heat. Stir-fry the chicken, in batches, until browned. Remove from the wok.

Add the garlic, ginger and sambal to the wok and stir-fry until fragrant. Return the nuts and chicken to the wok with the sauces and sherry and stir-fry until heated through. Add the onion and stir-fry until combined. Season to taste and serve.

title: chocolate and caramel cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a 12-hole muffin pan with paper liners.
In a large bowl, using an electric mixer, beat butter, sugar and vanilla together until pale and creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and cocoa together onto a plate. Fold into creamed mixture alternately with milk and choc chips, starting and finishing with flour.
Spoon mixture into the paper liners until 2/3 full. Bake for 15-20 minutes or until cooked when tested with a skewer. Cool in pan for 5 minutes, before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.

Meanwhile to make the caramel Icing, combine the brown sugar, butter and milk in a small saucepan. Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Cool. Stir in powdered sugar.
Spread icing over cakes. Top with fudge halves. Store in an airtight container.

title: lemon pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a 6 cup ovenproof dish. Cream butter and sugar. Add lemon zest and egg yolks. Add lemon juice and milk and mix well. Sift and fold in flour. Whip egg whites to soft peaks then fold in. Transfer to prepared dish then place dish in a roasting pan. Fill with hot water halfway up the side of the dish. Bake for 35 mins or until golden. Dust with powdered sugar. Serve immediately with mixed berries.

title: orange and limoncello squares
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a 12 x 17 inch baking tray. In a bowl, mix the flour, baking powder and orange zest. In a separate bowl, beat the egg yolks, 1 cup sugar and a pinch of salt. Gradually beat in oil and limoncello. Stir into the flour mixture.

Beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form, gradually adding 2/3 cup sugar. Fold into the egg yolk mixture in batches. Spoon into the pan and smooth. Arrange orange slices all over the top. Bake for 20-30 mins, until a skewer comes out clean.
Allow to cool on a wire rack. Cut into 24 squares and dust with powdered sugar.

title: toffee and banana cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Line a 12 cup muffin pan with paper liners. Mix flour, sugar, 1 tsp vanilla, baking powder and a pinch of salt. Add eggs, oil and buttermilk. Add bananas and 2 oz toffee bar crumbles. Distribute between liners and bake for 20-25 mins. Remove and let cool on a wire rack.
To serve, whip cream and add remaining vanilla extract. Decorate cupcakes with whipped cream and sprinkle with remaining toffee bar crumbles.

title: light fruit cake with almond crumble
directions: To make the almond crumble, place flour in a medium bowl. Cut in butter until crumbly. Stir in sugar, crumbled marzipan and nuts. Set aside.
Combine fruit and liqueur in a large bowl. Cover and let stand for 1 hour, or until most liquid is absorbed. Stir well.
Preheat oven to 300°F. Grease a 9x5 inch loaf pan and line base and sides with 2 layers of parchment paper, extending paper 2 inches above sides.

In a stand mixer, beat butter, vanilla and sugar until combined. Beat in eggs, 1 at a time then beat in sour cream. Fold in fruit mixture then ground almonds and flour. Transfer to prepared pan and smooth surface. Sprinkle with almond crumble and bake for 1 hour 45 mins. Cover with foil and let cool in pan.

title: chorizo,  sweet potato and brown rice stew
directions: Cook rice in a large pot of boiling, salted water according to packet instructions. Heat a large heavy-based saucepan on high. Cook chorizo for 1-2 mins or until browned on each side. Transfer to a plate.
Reduce heat to medium and add onion, garlic and paprika. Cook for 4-5 mins or until onion is tender.

Return chorizo to pan with tomatoes, chickpeas, sweet potato and water. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, then simmer for 10-15 mins or until sweet potato is just tender. Stir through 1/2 of the parsley and season to taste.
Stir remaining parsley through rice and serve with the hotpot.

title: steamed lemon puddings
directions: Lightly grease and line bases of 6 x 7 oz ramekins. Place 1 piece of lemon in the base of each ramekin.

In a small bowl, beat butter and sugar together until creamy. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Mix until mixture is pale and fluffy. Fold in flour, milk and lemon zest. Divide pudding batter between ramekins. Cover tightly with greased, pleated foil. Tie with kitchen string to seal.

Place in a large saucepan. Add enough boiling water to come halfway up the sides of the ramekins. Cover pan with a tight-fitting lid. Bring to a boil then reduce heat to low and simmer for 40 mins. Remove from pan and discard string and foil. Turn out onto serving plates and serve with custard.

title: no-bake granola bars
directions: Lightly grease and line a 7 x 10 inch baking pan with parchment paper, extending 2 inch over the long sides. In a large bowl, combine oats, coconut, sesame seeds, pumpkin seeds, apricots and cranberries. Mix well.

Heat butter, sugar and honey in a small saucepan. Stir for 2-3 mins, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer, without stirring, for 8-10 mins until caramelized. Pour over dry ingredients and stir until combined.
Spoon mixture into pan, pressing firmly with a metal spatula. Chill until firm. Cut into bars.

title: ravioli with asian greens
directions: Heat oil in wok on high heat. Stir-fry onions, ginger and garlic until onion has softened. Add ground chicken; stir-fry until lightly browned. Add half the soy sauce, five-spice and cabbage; stir-fry until cabbage is tender. Stir in cilantro; cool for 10 mins.
Place 1 level tbsp meat mixture in center of a wonton wrapper; brush around edges with water. Top with another wrapper; press edges together to seal. Repeat with remaining meat mixture and wrappers.

Add stock, chili peppers, barbecue sauce, cooking wine, remaining soy sauce and 1 1/2 cups water to same cleaned wok; bring to a boil. Add ravioli to wok; boil until it floats to the top. Using slotted spoon, remove from stock mixture; cover to keep warm.
Cook bok choy and snow peas in stock mixture until vegetables are tender.
Divide ravioli and vegetables among serving bowls; ladle stock mixture over the top.

title: vietnamese beef pho
directions: Pour the stock into a large saucepan and bring to a boil over a high heat. Add the ginger, cinnamon, star anise, sugar and coriander seeds and reduce the heat to medium. Simmer for 15 mins, then stir in the fish sauce. Season to taste with lemon juice and hoisin sauce.
Strain the broth through a large sieve and return to the saucepan over a high heat. Blanch the noodles in broth for 2 mins, until softened.
Divide the noodles among serving bowls. Top evenly with beef and beansprouts.
Ladle the hot broth into bowls. Serve with chili, herbs and green onion.

title: mushroom crostini with olive tapenade
directions: Place the garlic, olives and capers in a food processor and process until finely chopped. Transfer to a bowl and stir in 1/2 cup olive oil. Add a pinch of sugar and season to taste.

Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large frying pan. Briefly fry the bread on both sides, then remove and set aside. Heat 1 more tbsp oil and saute the mushrooms for 5-6 minutes. Season to taste, transfer to a bowl and set aside. Add onions to the pan and cook for 2-3 minutes. Stir in the parsley and season to taste.
Spread the tapenade on the toast, top with mushrooms and onions and serve.

title: roast lamb with greek herbs
directions: Mix the rosemary, oregano, lemon peel, sea salt and olive oil in a small bowl. Pour over the lamb. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or preferably overnight.

Preheat the oven to 400°F. Heat a large skillet on high heat. Cook the lamb for 3-5 mins on each side, or until seared. Transfer to a roasting pan and roast for 15-20 mins, or until cooked to desired doneness. Let stand for 10 mins, then slice.
Combine yogurt, tahini, lemon juice and salt in a small bowl. Serve lamb with arugula, pita bread and yogurt sauce.

title: chocolate orange cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease and line bottom of a 9-inch springform pan with parchment paper.

Beat egg yolks and sugar in a large bowl with an electric beater until pale and thick. Sift flour and baking powder into medium bowl. Fold into batter along with melted butter and orange peel and juice.
Beat egg whites in a medium bowl with electric mixer until soft peaks form. Fold into batter. Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 50 mins until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool in pan 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool 5 mins on wire rack.

Meanwhile, for the syrup, place orange juice, rum or brandy and sugar in a bowl. Stir briskly to dissolve sugar. Return cake to clean pan. Spoon syrup over warm cake. Let stand to cool completely. Transfer to a serving plate.

For the chocolate topping, place chocolate and coffee in a heatproof bowl. Place over a pan of simmering water on low heat. Stir continuously until chocolate melts. Remove from heat and whisk in sour cream, until smooth and glossy. Cool for 5 mins before spreading over cake.

title: mango and strawberry jam
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan. Stir on high heat, without boiling, until sugar dissolves. Bring to a boil; boil, uncovered, without stirring, about 30 mins or until jam jells when tested. (To test for a jam's setting point, place a small quantity of the mixture onto a saucer. Allow to cool. If it's ready, it will gel and wrinkle when moved.)
Pour hot jam into hot sterilized jars; seal immediately. Label and date jars when cold. Store in a cool dry place. Once opened, store in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate raisin cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Lightly grease a 9-inch tube pan.

Place raisins and 2 cups water in a medium saucepan on high heat. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 10 mins. Remove from heat. Stir in chocolate, cinnamon, baking soda, vanilla and cloves. Set aside to cool.
Beat butter and sugar in a large bowl with an electric mixer until creamy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flours together. Fold into egg mixture with raisin mixture, until well combined. Spoon into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 hour 10 mins. Cool in pan for 5 mins. Remove from pan; cool completely on a wire rack.
Meanwhile, for the chocolate glaze, melt chocolate and butter in a heatproof bowl set over a saucepan of gently simmering water, stirring until smooth. Pour over cake 30 mins before serving.

title: brown rice paella
directions: Bring rice, chicken stock, saffron and 2 cups water to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 40-45 mins, until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

Meanwhile, heat olive oil in a large frying pan over medium heat. Cook chorizo for 4-5 mins, until golden and crispy. Drain on paper towels. Add onion and garlic and saute for 3-4 mins, until tender. Add tomatoes, paprika and green beans. Simmer for 2 mins. Add chorizo, chicken, peppers and rice.
Serve garnished with parsley.

title: pancakes with honey
directions: In a saucepan, melt the butter. Transfer to a bowl then add the milk, sugar, flour and a pinch of salt and beat until smooth. Beat in the eggs. Allow to rest for 15 mins.

Coat an 7 inch diameter non-stick frying pan with cooking spray and heat. Pour 1/8 of the batter into the pan and swirl. Cook for 2 mins on each side, remove from the pan and keep warm. Repeat with the remaining batter and serve drizzled with the honey.

title: chunky chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.

Combine sugar, flour and nuts in a large bowl. Combine butter, egg, egg yolk and vanilla then mix into dry ingredients until just combined. Stir in chocolate. Shape into balls, each around 2 tbsp, and place 2 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased baking trays. Bake for 16 mins, or until lightly browned. Let cool on trays.

title: fruit salad with honey ricotta and almonds
directions: Toast the almonds in a dry skillet over a medium heat until golden brown then set aside. Mix all the fruit pieces together in a bowl.
Whisk together the ricotta cheese, milk and honey then pour over the mixed fruit. Top with toasted almonds.

title: curry and lime lentil soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan. Cook curry paste, stirring, until fragrant. Add onion, garlic, ginger and cumin. Cook, stirring, until onion has softened. Add lentils, stock, tomatoes and 2 1/2 cups water. Bring to a boil then reduce heat and simmer for 20 mins, or until lentils are softened.
Stir in lime zest and juice. Return to a boil then remove from heat and stir in parsley.

title: fettuccine with crispy pork and mushrooms
directions: For the croutons and pork, preheat oven to 400°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Arrange bread and pork in a single layer on baking sheet. Drizzle with 2 tbsp oil and season. Bake 10-12 mins, until crisp.
Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package instructions. Drain well and return to pan.

For the sauce, heat remaining oil in a large frying pan on medium. Fry mushrooms 3-4 mins, until golden. Add marsala and cook, stirring, 1 min, until reduced by half. Add stock and simmer 2-3 mins, until reduced by half. Stir in currants and thyme. Add to pasta along with croutons and pork, tossing well. Season to taste and serve immediately.

title: strawberry yogurt with muesli and berries
directions: Distribute berries between 4 serving glasses. Distribute yogurt over top then sprinkle with muesli. Serve immediately.

title: roasted fish with sweet potato wontons and pea purée
directions: Cook the sweet potatoes in boiling water for about 15-17 mins, until soft. To make the peas, melt the butter in a saucepan and saute the shallots. Add the peas and sprinkle them with sugar. Pour in the wine and stock, add the cream and simmer for about 5 mins. Season the mixture to taste, remove it from the stove and puree.

To make the wontons, drain the sweet potatoes and press them through a potato ricer. Season them with lime zest, salt, pepper, chili pepper and some of the lime juice. Whisk the egg white. Spread the wonton wrappers out on a clean surface. Spread the sweet potato mixture evenly in the middle of the wrappers. Brush the edges with egg white, then fold into triangles and pinch to seal. Heat the vegetable oil in a large saucepan and fry the wontons in batches for 2-3 mins, until golden brown. Remove from oil with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.

Heat the olive oil in a frying pan and fry the fish for 5 mins, turning. Add the garlic and herbs and season to taste. Remove the fish from the pan and slice it. Arrange on 4 plates with the wontons, herbs and pea puree.

title: tagliatelle bolognese
directions: Heat butter or oil in a medium saucepan on medium heat. Cook onion, carrot, celery and bacon or pancetta until soft and turning golden.
Add the ground beef; cook until browned. Add the wine; cook until completely evaporated. Add the tomatoes, tomato paste and half the stock. Season with salt and black pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 2 hours. Add a little more stock if mixture becomes too dry.
Cook the pasta in a large saucepan of boiling salted water according to package directions. Season bolognese and serve with drained pasta.

title: white and sweet potato mash
directions: Cook russet potatoes in a large saucepan of boiling water for 10 mins. Add sweet potatoes; continue cooking for 10 mins until both potatoes are tender.
Drain; mash. Fold in butter, seasoning, garlic and thyme. Season to taste. Serve with jerk chicken.

title: pork chops with spinach and tomato sauce
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°F. Place a sprig of rosemary on each pork chop. Wrap a slice of bacon around each one. Secure with a toothpick if necessary.

Heat the oil in a large skillet on medium-high heat. Cook the pork chops, turning, for 8 mins. Remove from the pan and season with black pepper. Add the onion and garlic to the pan and saute until softened. Add the tomato paste and cook for 1 min. Add the tomatoes, breaking them up with a wooden spoon. Add the cream and season with salt, black pepper and a pinch of sugar. Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 mins.

Blanch the spinach in boiling salted water for 1 min. Drain and refresh with cold water. Stir into the tomato sauce. Spoon 2/3 of the sauce into baking dish. Arrange the pork chops on top. Pour the remaining sauce over the pork chops.
Bake for 15 mins. Garnish with rosemary and serve with baguette.

title: creamed corn and pumpkin mash
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Remove corn kernels from cobs. Place in a saucepan with cream over moderate heat and simmer 8 minutes or until corn is tender and sauce has thickened slightly. Set aside.

Meanwhile, place pumpkin, garlic and oil on prepared tray and toss to coat. Season with salt and pepper. Bake 20 minutes. Add walnuts and bake 10 minutes more or until golden and cooked. Cool 10 minutes. Set walnuts aside.
Squeeze garlic from skins. Add garlic and pumpkin to corn mixture and mash until smooth. Stir in half the walnuts. Serve sprinkled with remaining walnuts.

title: breakfast beans with bacon, sausages and eggs
directions: Heat oil in a frying pan. Cook bacon, onion and garlic, stirring, until onion softens. Add tomatoes, 1 cup water, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard powder and beans. Cook, covered, for 20 mins.
Meanwhile, cook sausages and eggs in an oiled frying pan until sausages are cooked through and egg white has set.
Serve beans with sausages and eggs.

title: ribollita italian soup
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven on medium heat. Add the onion, celery, carrot, garlic, pancetta and thyme. Cook for about 5 mins or until the vegetables have softened but are not colored.
Add the stock and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; add the beans and simmer for 30 mins or until the beans are tender.
Add the tomatoes, zucchini, kale and bread and simmer for a further 15 mins.
Season the soup to taste with salt and pepper. Turn off the heat and let stand for 10 mins.
Serves with a generous drizzle of extra virgin olive oil and Parmesan cheese on the side.

title: key lime pie
directions: Grease a 9 inch fluted tart pan with removable bottom with 1 tbsp of the oil. Place the remaining oil and chocolate in a small saucepan. Cook on low heat, stirring, until chocolate melts. Place the cornflakes and ladyfingers in a freezer bag and crush finely using a rolling pin. Mix the chocolate mixture and crumbs then press into the tart pan. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

Measure out 2/3 cup lime juice and 1 tbsp lime juice separately. Refrigerate the egg whites. Place the condensed milk, cream, butter, 1/2 cup of the sugar, 1 cup water and 1 tbsp of the lime peel in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, stirring.
Mix the 2/3 cup lime juice and cornstarch together. Remove the pan from the heat and mix in the lime juice mixture. Return to the stove and bring to a boil, stirring. Remove from the heat.

Beat 6 egg yolks in a bowl. Stir in 1-2 tbsp hot lime cream. Stir the egg yolks into the remaining lime cream in the pan. Spread the mixture in the prepared crust. Set aside to cool for 30 mins then refrigerate for 2 hours.

Beat the egg whites in a bowl with an electric mixer on medium speed until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in 1 1/4 cups sugar. Continue to beat until the mixture is stiff and glossy. Stir in reserved 1 tbsp lime juice. Use a spatula to loosely spread the meringue on the top of the pie. Use a kitchen blowtorch to caramelize the meringue.

title: roast chicken and gravy with rice pilaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Rub chicken with 1 tbsp oil, salt and pepper and tie the legs together with kitchen twine. Place in a roasting pan and roast for 1 hour 15 mins. Combine 1 tbsp oil and the paprika and use to baste the chicken a few times as it is cooking.

Cook the rice in boiling salted water according to the package instructions. When the rice is nearly done, blanch the carrots in salted water for 3 mins, adding the peas after 2 mins. Drain the vegetables. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a large pan and saute the mushrooms for 3 mins, then add the carrots and peas and cook another 2-3 mins. Add the drained rice and cook for 5 mins, then stir in half of the marjoram.

Remove the chicken from the oven, allow to rest, and carve, taking care to retain the juices. Bring 1 1/2 cups water to a gentle boil and add chicken juices. Thicken with cornflour and season. Arrange the rice and chicken on plates, pour the gravy on top and sprinkle with the remaining marjoram.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook the pasta in a large saucepan of boiling water according to package directions. Add the green beans to the pan for the last 2 mins of pasta cooking time, then drain. Rinse under cold water.
For the dressing, whisk the chili pepper, oil, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl.
Combine the pasta, green beans, herbs, tomato, pepper, tuna and dressing in a large bowl and toss gently.

title: heart cake and cookies
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°F. Grease a 9 cup heart-shaped cake pan and sprinkle with flour. To make the cake, beat 1 cup + 2 tbsp butter, 1 1/4 cup sugar, 2 tsp vanilla extract and a pinch of salt with the whisk of a mixer until creamy. Beat in the eggs one at a time, then beat in the liqueur. Sift in 2 cups flour and 3 tsp baking powder and fold to combine. Pour into the pan and smooth the top. Bake for 50 mins, or until a skewer comes out clean, covering with aluminum foil after 30 mins. Remove from the oven and increase the temperature to 400°F. Cool for 10 mins, then turn out of the pan and cool completely.

Meanwhile, to make the cookie dough, mix the remaining flour, sugar, and vanilla extract with a pinch of salt and a pinch of baking powder. Cut 4 tbsp butter into small pieces and add to the dough along with 1 egg yolk. Knead with the dough hook of a mixer, then with your hands until smooth. Chill for 30 mins.

On a lightly floured work surface, roll out the cookie dough and cut out different-sized hearts. Lay on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Beat the cream and 1 egg yolk and brush over the cookies. Bake for 7 mins then allow to cool.

Melt the chocolate in a heatproof bowl set over a pan of simmering water. Spread on the cake. Use the writing icing to decorate the cookies with names and hearts. Arrange on the cake. Decorate with heart sprinkles to serve.

title: souvlaki with greek salad
directions: To make the tzatziki sauce, mix the grated cucumber, garlic and yogurt and season. Cover and chill in the fridge.
To make the salad, mix the remaining cucumber, tomatoes, olives, feta, diced onion and diced red bell pepper. Toss with the vinegar and 1 tbsp oil. Season to taste, cover and set aside.
For the souvlaki, thread the pork, remaining onion and bell peppers onto skewers. Season well.
Heat the remaining oil in a large frying pan and sear the skewers for 8-10 mins, turning frequently, until the pork is cooked through and lightly charred in places. Serve with the salad and tzatziki.

title: hot bratwurst rolls
directions: Brush inside of rolls with melted butter and sprinkle with green onions and herbs.
Grill sausages over medium heat for 5 mins. Place 1 sausage inside each roll. Wrap rolls tightly in foil and chill until required.
When ready to serve, bake rolls in a 350°F oven for 15 mins. Serve topped with mustard.

title: rice flour molten chocolate cakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°F. Spray four 1/2-cup ramekins with the cooking spray.
Place the chocolate and butter in a heatproof bowl over a saucepan of simmering water (don't let base of bowl touch the water). Stir until melted and smooth. Remove the bowl from the heat.

Whisk egg yolks, eggs and sugar in a large bowl. Add the chocolate mixture; stir until well blended. Add the rice flour; stir gently to combine. Spoon mixture evenly into the prepared ramekins. Place on a baking pan.
Bake for 8 mins. Let stand for 2 mins. Unmold cakes onto serving plates. Serve topped with the whipped cream and mint leaves.

title: warm crisp egg salad with fries
directions: Bake the fries according to package directions.
For the dressing, whisk all ingredients in a small bowl.
Meanwhile, gently lower eggs into a saucepan of water. Bring to a boil on high heat. Reduce heat to medium; simmer for 3-4 mins. Transfer to a bowl of iced water. Carefully peel eggs and pat dry.

Heat oil in a saucepan on medium heat, until a small cube of bread sizzles as soon as it is added. Gently lower eggs, one at time, into oil. Deep-fry 1 min, until golden and crisp. Drain on a paper towel.
Arrange endive on plates. Top with halved eggs and drizzle with dressing. Serve with sliced chili pepper and fries.

title: roasted feta with olives
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F.

In a small baking dish, arrange sun-dried tomatoes in a triangle. Place feta directly on top. Arrange tomatoes, garlic and olives around feta and sprinkle with rosemary. Drizzle sun-dried tomato oil over feta. Drizzle olive oil over other ingredients. Bake for 15-20 mins, or until feta is lightly browned. Serve immediately with crusty bread.

title: cured sausage salad
directions: For the croutons, heat 2 tbsp oil in a frying pan, add the bread and toast, turning, for 3 mins.

Meanwhile, whisk together the vinegar and remaining oil. Season to taste with salt, pepper, and sugar. Mix in the chives and horseradish. Toss with the remaining ingredients and serve sprinkled with croutons.

title: low-fat yogurt berry pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine crushed meringues, berries, yogurt and pudding. Spoon mixture evenly into 4 serving glasses. Sprinkle with hazelnuts. Serve immediately.

title: linguine with white anchovies and sicilian olives
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water until al dente. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup pasta water.
Meanwhile, heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a frying pan over medium-high heat. Add 1 tsp garlic and breadcrumbs. Cook for 3-4 mins, until crisp and golden, tossing occasionally. Season.

Wipe out frying pan. Reduce heat to medium and add remaining oil. Cook anchovies for 2 mins then mash into oil with a fork. Add remaining garlic and chili flakes. Cook for 2 mins. Increase heat to high, add olives, pasta and reserved pasta water and toss to combine. Cook for 1-2 mins, until sauce thickens.
Distribute between serving bowls and top with breadcrumbs, basil and Parmesan cheese.

title: fig and blue cheese tartlets
directions: Preheat oven to 425°F. Line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.

Cut seven 3 inch rounds from each sheet of pastry and place on prepared baking sheets. Score around edge of each round with a knife, 1/2 inch from edge. Prick centers with a fork. Brush with egg and bake for 10 mins, until puffed and lightly golden.
Remove from oven and press center of each pastry round down. Spoon a little blue cheese into center and top with a fig half, cut-side up. Bake for 10 mins. Serve topped with a sprig of thyme.

title: tuna, pepper and olive bruschetta
directions: Combine tuna, peppers, olives, basil and vinegar in a medium bowl.
Preheat a grill pan on medium heat. Spray both sides of bread with no stick cooking spray. Grill for 1 min each side or until toasted. Rub bread with garlic.
Spread bread with ricotta. Top with tuna mixture. Serve at once.

title: mesquite lime marinated steak
directions: Combine 1/2 cup marinade, 1/2 tsp lime zest, 2 tbsp lime juice and 2 tbsp oil. Add beef and marinate for 2 hours, turning occasionally.
Preheat grill. Cook beef over medium-high heat for 10-12 mins, turning once, or until cooked to your liking.
Meanwhile, combine corn, red pepper, scallion, jalapeno, herbs and garlic. Add remaining marinade, oil, 1/2 tsp lime zest and 2 tbsp lime juice. Season. Let marinate for 30 mins. Serve with steak.

title: german fish pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°F. Place potatoes in a medium saucepan, cover with cold water and bring to a boil over medium heat. Reduce heat and simmer for 15 mins, or until tender. Drain. Mash until smooth. Add cheese and 1/4 cup butter. Set aside.

Meanwhile, heat remaining chopped butter in a large saucepan. Add leek, fennel and garlic. Cook for 5-7 mins, or until vegetables soften. Add flour and stir to combine. Gradually add milk, stirring. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 5 mins, or until sauce thickens.

Add fish and simmer for 5 mins, or until just cooked. Remove from heat. Add cream, parsley and 1 tbsp reserved fennel fronds. Transfer to a deep baking dish and top with mashed potatoes. Brush top with melted butter and bake for 30 mins, or until lightly browned and heated through.

title: brie stuffed chicken with cranberry sauce and spinach
directions: Cut a 1 inch slit in the thick end of each chicken breast. Carefully push the knife through to make a pocket, without cutting all the way through. Push some of the cheese into the pocket and secure with toothpicks.
Stir the spinach in a heated, oiled frying pan, 2-3 mins, until wilted. Season, remove from pan and cover to keep warm.
Cook the chicken in the same pan, 5-7 mins, until cooked through. Remove from pan. Cover and set aside 5 mins. Serve on a bed of spinach with the cranberry sauce.

title: cranberry and almond stollen
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups of the almonds, chopped cranberries, orange and lemon peels, and rum in a medium bowl. Cover and set aside.

Place the flour in a large mixer bowl. Make a well in the center and add the yeast. Heat the milk until lukewarm and pour over the yeast. Sprinkle with some of the flour. Cover and let stand in a warm place for 15 mins.

Add the granulated sugar, 14 tbsp (1 3/4 sticks) of the butter and a pinch of salt to the flour mixture. Mix with the dough hook of an electric mixer until smooth. Cover and let stand in a warm place for 45 mins.

Preheat the oven to 325°F. Knead the almond mixture into the dough. On a lightly floured surface, roll out the dough to a 18 x 12 inch rectangle. Fold the dough into thirds from the long side. Press down. Place the stollen on a parchment paper lined baking sheet.

Bake for 1 hour or until a skewer inserted into the center comes out clean. Melt remaining 8 tbsp (1 stick) butter and brush 1/3 on the hot stollen. Sprinkle with 1/3 of the powdered sugar. Repeat twice with the remaining butter and powdered sugar. Sprinkle with the 2 tbsp cranberries and remaining 1/4 cup chopped almonds. Transfer stollen to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: creamy bacon and mushroom pasta
directions: Cook pasta in lightly salted, boiling water for 12-15 mins, until al dente.

Meanwhile, heat olive oil and butter in a large frying pan. Cook pancetta until crispy. Set aside. Add garlic and mushrooms and cook, stirring, until browned. Add white wine and simmer until 1/2 the liquid has evaporated. Add creme fraiche and heat gently, stirring until smooth. Return pancetta to sauce. Season.
Drain pasta and toss with sauce. Add basil and toss to combine. Serve immediately with Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: veal cutlets with polenta and sage tomatoes
directions: Bring stock and milk to a boil in a large saucepan. Gradually stir in polenta. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, for 8 mins, or until polenta thickens. Stir in 1/2 cup Parmesan and season to taste.

Preheat broiler. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a large frying pan over high heat. Press 2 sage leaves onto each veal cutlet. Cook for 3 mins per side, or until cooked to your liking. Remove from pan, cover and let rest for 5 mins.

Combine tomatoes and remaining sage leaves and oil in a small baking dish. Season. Broil for 5 mins, or until tomato skins burst. Serve veal with polenta and sage tomatoes. Sprinkle with remaining Parmesan.

title: almond-crusted trout
directions: Season the fish with salt and black pepper. Roll in the flour and tap off any excess. Dip in the egg, then roll in the almonds.

Melt 2 tbsp butter in each of 2 frying pans and fry 2 trouts per pan over a medium heat for 5-6 mins per side. Arrange on plates and drizzle over the cooking juices. Serve with boiled potatoes and a green salad.

title: lemongrass pork and prawn skewers
directions: In a food processor, process prawns until finely chopped. Add pork, ginger, garlic, 2 tbsp cilantro, palm sugar and 1/4 tsp salt. Process until combined. Lightly bruise lemongrass stalks to release flavor. Divide pork mixture into 8 portions and shape around lemongrass stalks. Place on a baking tray lined with plastic wrap, cover and chill for 30 mins.
Meanwhile, to make the dipping sauce, combine fish sauce, lime juice, honey, remaining cilantro and finely chopped lemongrass. Transfer to a serving bowl and set aside.
Preheat broiler. Lightly coat lemongrass skewers with oil and broil for 8-10 mins, turning occasionally, until cooked through. Serve with dipping sauce, lime wedges and cilantro.

title: lamb and couscous stir-fry
directions: Place couscous in a small bowl; stir in 3/4 cup boiling water. Cover and let stand for 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Add cilantro; fluff with a fork to separate grains.
Heat a wok or large skillet on high heat. Add oil; swirl to coat bottom and sides. Stir-fry lamb for 1-2 mins or until browned. Add onion and zucchini; stir-fry for 1-2 mins or until just tender.
Add spices, couscous and salt; stir-fry for 1 min or until heated through.
Mix yogurt and garlic in a bowl. Spoon lamb mixture into serving bowls. Serve topped with yogurt.

title: apricot and almond granola bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°F. Line a baking tray with parchment paper. Mix butter, honey and cinnamon until smooth. Toss with almonds, oats, muesli, flour and apricots. Fold in egg white. Transfer to prepared pan and form into an 8x12 inch rectangle. Bake for 25 mins, until golden brown and firm to the touch. Let cool for 10 mins then cut into 20 bars.

title: mediterranean fish soup
directions: Heat oil in large saucepan on medium heat. Cook fennel, onion and garlic until vegetables soften. Add saffron, tomato paste and wine; cook for 2 mins, stirring.
Add tomatoes, stock, 2 1/2 cups water, thyme and sage to pan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 20 mins.
In batches, blend or process soup until smooth. Return soup to same pan; bring to a boil. Add mussels, fish and squid. Cover and simmer about 3 mins or until mussels open.
Divide soup among serving bowls. Sprinkle with basil.

title: spaghetti with artichokes, asparagus and peas
directions: Cook pasta in boiling salted water for 8 mins, or until al dente. Drain.

Meanwhile, heat olive oil in a large frying pan over medium-high heat. Cook asparagus and garlic, stirring, for about 2 mins, or until asparagus is just tender. Add peas and artichokes. Cook for 2 mins.
Add drained spaghetti to asparagus mixture and stir until heated through. Serve pasta topped with ricotta.

title: grilled scallops and chanterelle mushrooms
directions: Preheat your oven's broiler. Season the scallops with salt and black pepper and roll in the flour, tapping off any excess. Heat 2 tbsp oil in a frying pan and saute the scallops, turning, for 2-3 mins. Remove and drain on paper towels.
Add 1 tbsp oil to the pan and saute the mushrooms for 3-4 mins. Add 3/4 of the parsley and season with salt and black pepper. Spoon into 4 ovenproof ramekins and add 2 scallops to each.
Add the cream to the pan and simmer for 1-2 mins. Pour into the ramekins and broil for 5 mins, until golden brown. Sprinkle with the remaining parsley to serve.

title: grilled pork with herbed polenta
directions: Bring 4 cups water to a boil in a medium saucepan. Remove from heat. Add the salt and 3 tbsp of the butter. Stir in the polenta with a wooden spoon. Return to the heat. Cook, stirring constantly, until the polenta thickens. Reduce the heat to low and simmer for 10 mins, stirring frequently. Stir in the parsley, thyme and nutmeg. Grease a 12 x 8 inch baking pan with 1 tsp of the oil. Spoon in the polenta. Smooth the top with a spatula. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Crush the peppercorns, coriander and fennel with a mortar and pestle. Mix with the breadcrumbs, paprika and remaining 1 tbsp butter, melted. Season with salt. Set aside.
Place the vinegar in a bowl and season with salt, black pepper and a pinch of sugar. Gradually whisk in 2 tbsp of the oil. Toss with the salad.

Season the pork with salt and black pepper. Heat 1 tsp of the oil in a nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Cook the pork for 6-8 mins until golden, turning once. Remove from the skillet and keep warm. Pour the wine into the skillet and simmer until reduced by half. Add the stock and cream and simmer for 2 mins. Season with salt and black pepper. Keep warm.
Preheat the broiler. Cut the polenta into diamond shapes. Heat the remaining 1 tsp oil in a skillet on medium heat. Cook the polenta in batches until lightly browned on both sides.
Sprinkle the pork chops with the breadcrumb mixture. Broil for 1 min. Serve with the polenta, sauce and salad.

title: coconut chicken soup with cilantro and rice
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan over medium heat. Add spices and chicken. Cook, stirring, for 2-3 mins, until browned. Add flour and cook, stirring, for 1 min. Add stock and simmer for 5-6 mins, until sauce thickens slightly.
Add rice, lemon juice and coconut milk. Season. Simmer for 3 mins. Add chopped cilantro and ladle into bowls to serve.

title: beef in asian broth
directions: Combine 6 cups water, stock, ginger, soy sauce and sesame oil in a large saucepan; bring to a boil. Add the noodles; using a fork, separate the noodles. Reduce the heat to low; simmer, uncovered, until the noodles are just tender.
Add the remaining ingredients; stir until heated through and the beef is cooked to desired doneness.

title: chicken with brandy and grape sauce over polenta
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Place garlic on a small tray in the oven while it is preheating. Season flour then dredge chicken, shaking off excess. Heat oil in a large Dutch oven, add chicken and cook until browned all over. Add garlic then transfer to oven. Bake, uncovered, for 25 mins.

Meanwhile, bring 2 1/2 cups water and milk to a boil in a medium pot. Gradually whisk in polenta and cook, stirring, for about 10 mins or until thickened. Add butter and cheese and stir until cheese melts. Set aside.

Remove chicken from oven, add thyme and bake for another 10 mins or until chicken is tender. Transfer Dutch oven to stove, remove chicken and garlic from pan, cover, and keep warm. Add brandy and wine to Dutch oven and bring to a boil. Add 1/4 cup water, reduce heat and simmer, stirring, until thickened slightly. Add grapes.
Serve chicken over polenta with brandy and grape sauce.

title: teriyaki beef burgers
directions: In a shallow dish, combine beef and teriyaki. Cover and marinate for 30 mins.
Heat oil in a large wok over high heat. Working in batches, stir-fry beef for 2-3 mins, or until cooked to your liking.
Spread mayonnaise over rolls and top with mixed greens. Divide beef between rolls. Combine remaining ingredients then sprinkle over sandwiches to serve.

title: marinated lamb fillets with creamy polenta
directions: Place lamb fillets in a bowl with oregano, oil and garlic. Season to taste then chill for 10 mins.
Meanwhile, bring stock to a boil. Gradually whisk in polenta. Cook, stirring, for 10 mins. Add Parmesan and sour cream. Season. Keep warm.
Heat a large, oiled frying pan over high heat. Cook lamb for 2-3 mins per side, or until cooked to your liking. Remove from pan and let rest, covered, for 5 mins.
Add jelly and 1/4 cup water to pan. Simmer for 4-5 mins, until thickened slightly.
Arrange polenta, spinach and tomatoes on serving plates. Top with lamb and drizzle with red currant sauce. Serve immediately.

title: pork chops with zucchini and potato mash
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan with enough salted water to cover. Bring to a boil. Cook for 12-15 mins, until tender. Add zucchini for the last 5 mins. Drain and return to the pan.
Meanwhile, season pork chops with cracked black pepper. Spray with no stick cooking spray. Heat a large skillet on high heat. Cook pork chops for 4 mins each side, until cooked to desired doneness.
Mash vegetables. Stir in garlic and milk. Season to taste. Serve with pork chops.

title: sweet potato, red pepper and lentil soup
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Toss sweet potato in a baking dish with half the oil. Season to taste. Bake 15 mins. Add pepper, tomatoes, onion and garlic. Toss with remaining oil and bake 15-20 more mins.

Transfer mixture to a large saucepan. Add stock. Bring to a boil on high. Reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, 15 mins. Puree using a hand blender or food processor. Stir in lentils. Reheat in saucepan. Serve with a dollop of yogurt, basil leaves and crusty bread.

title: zucchini and halloumi fritters
directions: Place the grated zucchini in a colander, sprinkle with salt and leave for 30 mins.
Squeeze out the excess moisture and pat dry with paper towels.
Place the zucchini, shallots, mint, parsley, halloumi and eggs in a bowl and mix to combine. Sift in the flour, mix, and season to taste.
Heat oil in a large, non-stick frying pan over a medium heat. When hot, add tablespoons of the zucchini mixture.
Flatten the fritters slightly in the pan and cook for 2-3 mins each side or until golden brown. Transfer to paper towels and repeat with remaining batter.
To serve, arrange the fritters on a serving plate with lemon wedges on the side.

title: blueberry pancakes
directions: Sift the flour, sugar and baking soda into a large bowl. Whisk the egg, buttermilk and butter in a medium bowl. Gradually stir into the flour mixture until smooth.

Spray a large skillet with no stick cooking spray and heat to medium. Place 4 heaping tablespoons of batter into the pan to make 4 pancakes. Sprinkle each one with a few blueberries. Cook for 2 mins, until bubbles appear on the surface. Turn and cook for 30 seconds, until lightly browned. Remove to a plate and cover to keep warm. Cook the remaining batter to make 24 pancakes.
Serve the pancakes with a dollop of yogurt and additional blueberries on top.

title: anchovy and chili lamb chops with creamy polenta
